WEBVTT

00:54.855 --> 00:57.125
[CAMERA CLICKS]

00:57.925 --> 00:59.127
[CLICK]

01:00.561 --> 01:02.930
[WINDING]

01:02.930 --> 01:05.132
[CLICKING]

01:29.123 --> 01:31.392
[DOOR BUZZES]

01:39.933 --> 01:41.001
[OPENS DOOR]

01:41.001 --> 01:42.670
Man: PACKAGE FOR
ROBERT GARFIELD?

01:42.670 --> 01:44.238
YEAH.
SIGN HERE.

01:44.238 --> 01:46.707
THANKS.
[DOOR CLOSES]

02:42.162 --> 02:43.564
Bobby: WHENEVER IT WANTS,

02:43.564 --> 02:47.868
THE PAST CAN COME KICKING
THE DOOR DOWN.

02:47.868 --> 02:52.440
AND...YOU NEVER KNOW
WHERE IT'S GONNA TAKE YOU.

02:52.440 --> 02:56.477
ALL YOU CAN DO IS HOPE
IT'S A PLACE YOU WANT TO GO.

03:07.120 --> 03:10.691
Bobby on machine: HI. YOU'VE
REACHED THE GARFIELD FAMILY.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.726
JILL AND THE BOYS
ARE AWAY SKIING.

03:12.726 --> 03:15.429
YOU CAN REACH THEM ON
THEIR VARIOUS CELL PHONES.

03:15.429 --> 03:18.499
ME, I'M GONNA BE ON
THE ROAD FOR A FEW DAYS.

03:18.499 --> 03:20.934
BE BACK TUESDAY.
[BEEP]

03:20.934 --> 03:22.936
[KEYS JINGLE]

03:24.305 --> 03:25.739
[DOOR CLOSES]

03:25.739 --> 03:27.808
ON BEHALF OF THE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES

03:27.808 --> 03:29.810
AND THE PEOPLE
OF A GRATEFUL NATION,

03:29.810 --> 03:32.513
I PRESENT THIS FLAG AS
A TOKEN OF APPRECIATION

03:32.513 --> 03:34.648
FOR THE HONORABLE AND
FAITHFUL SERVICE RENDERED

03:34.648 --> 03:36.850
BY YOUR HUSBAND,
MAJOR JOHN SULLIVAN,

03:36.850 --> 03:38.419
KNOWN AS SULLY.

03:38.419 --> 03:41.622
Boy: HEY, SULLY!
HEY!

03:41.622 --> 03:43.357
Sully: BOBBY,
I DECIDED LAST NIGHT

03:43.357 --> 03:44.625
WHAT I WANT TO BE
WHEN I GROW UP.

03:44.625 --> 03:45.859
WHAT'S THAT?
A MAGICIAN!

03:45.859 --> 03:47.695
I'LL PULL RABBITS
AND SHIT OUT OF A HAT!

03:47.695 --> 03:50.498
RABBITS WILL PROBABLY
SHIT IN YOUR HAT.

03:50.498 --> 03:52.966
BUT I'D BE A COOL BASTARD.
COME ON, ADMIT IT.

03:52.966 --> 03:54.835
[ECHOING LAUGHTER]

03:54.835 --> 03:57.505
[TAPS PLAYING]

04:04.044 --> 04:07.247
THERE'S CAKE AND COFFEE
AT THE VETERANS' HALL.

04:07.247 --> 04:10.284
OF COURSE,
YOU'RE ALL WELCOME.

04:10.284 --> 04:13.253
[LOW CONVERSATION]

04:13.253 --> 04:15.289
MR. GARFIELD.
MR. OLIVER.

04:15.289 --> 04:16.624
HELLO.
HI.

04:16.624 --> 04:17.858
THANKS FOR
SENDING THE GLOVE.

04:17.858 --> 04:20.327
BEEN SULLY'S LAWYER
SINCE FOREVER.

04:20.327 --> 04:21.562
COULDN'T FOR THE LIFE
OF ME SEE WHY

04:21.562 --> 04:24.798
A BASEBALL GLOVE
HAD TO GO THROUGH PROBATE.

04:24.798 --> 04:28.669
YOU AND SULLY
WERE KIDS TOGETHER?

04:28.669 --> 04:30.671
YEAH.
THERE WERE 3 OF US.

04:30.671 --> 04:32.272
WELL, THERE WAS
ME AND SULLY

04:32.272 --> 04:34.141
AND THERE WAS
A GIRL NAMED CAROL.

04:34.141 --> 04:36.143
CAROL GERBER?
THAT'S RIGHT.

04:36.143 --> 04:38.412
YEAH. I'M HOPING
SHE'LL BE HERE.

04:38.412 --> 04:42.583
YOU DIDN'T HEAR
ABOUT CAROL?

04:44.852 --> 04:46.019
NO.

04:50.190 --> 04:52.893
I'M AFRAID SHE'S DEAD.

04:54.362 --> 04:57.297
I'M SO SORRY.

04:57.297 --> 04:59.500
[GASPING]

05:06.807 --> 05:09.377
[SIGHS]

05:39.039 --> 05:42.543
Bobby: THIS STREET
IS WHERE IT ALL HAPPENED.

05:42.543 --> 05:44.812
IT'S NOT MUCH NOW.

05:44.812 --> 05:50.083
WHY DO WE ALWAYS EXPECT
HOME WILL STAY THE SAME?

05:50.083 --> 05:53.421
NOTHING ELSE DOES.

06:03.063 --> 06:04.364
[LOCK RATTLES]

06:04.364 --> 06:06.366
IT'S FUNNY
HOW WHEN YOU'RE A KID

06:06.366 --> 06:09.603
A DAY CAN LAST FOREVER.

06:09.603 --> 06:15.075
NOW...ALL THESE YEARS
SEEMED JUST LIKE A BLINK.

06:15.075 --> 06:16.444
[TRAIN HORN BLOWS]

06:16.444 --> 06:18.245
[TRAIN RATTLING]

06:18.245 --> 06:20.914
[THUD]

06:20.914 --> 06:22.916
[CREAKING]

06:28.989 --> 06:30.991
[FLOORBOARDS CREAKING]

06:50.911 --> 06:52.713
[EXHALES]

06:59.487 --> 07:03.657
Liz: BOBBY! BOBBY-O!
TIME TO GET A WIGGLE ON!

07:03.657 --> 07:05.493
WAKE UP, BOBBY!

07:05.493 --> 07:07.094
[BICYCLE BELL RINGS]

07:07.094 --> 07:08.095
[GIGGLING]

07:08.095 --> 07:09.563
Girl:
HEY, WAIT FOR ME!

07:09.563 --> 07:11.565
[KIDS LAUGHING]

07:11.565 --> 07:15.135
[BELL RINGS]
COME ON, JOHNNY!

07:15.135 --> 07:16.336
[EXHALES]

07:16.336 --> 07:18.405
* YOU BROKE *

07:18.405 --> 07:20.407
* MY HEART *

07:20.407 --> 07:22.309
* WHEN YOU SAID *

07:22.309 --> 07:23.410
* WE'LL PART *

07:23.410 --> 07:24.444
* AIN'T THAT... *

07:24.444 --> 07:27.615
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, MR. 11.
TA-DA!

07:35.422 --> 07:39.159
OH, WOW.
A LIBRARY CARD.

07:39.159 --> 07:42.663
A GROWN-UP'S LIBRARY CARD,
IF YOU PLEASE.

07:44.832 --> 07:48.468
[SIGHS] THANKS, MOM.
IT'S--

07:48.468 --> 07:49.903
JUST DON'T.

07:49.903 --> 07:52.706
DON'T YOU THINK I WANTED
TO GET YOU A BIKE?

07:52.706 --> 07:54.608
I CAN'T AFFORD IT.

07:54.608 --> 07:56.343
DO YOU KNOW HOW
THAT MAKES ME FEEL?

07:56.343 --> 07:59.346
YOUR FATHER DIDN'T EXACTLY
LEAVE US WELL OFF, YOU KNOW.

07:59.346 --> 08:00.714
I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT HE DID LEAVE US.

08:00.714 --> 08:02.650
HE LEFT US
3 MONTHS UNPAID RENT,

08:02.650 --> 08:03.917
A LIFE INSURANCE POLICY

08:03.917 --> 08:06.486
THAT LAPSED THE YEAR
BEFORE HE DIED.

08:06.486 --> 08:10.123
HE LEFT A RATHER LARGE
STACK OF UNPAID BILLS

08:10.123 --> 08:12.459
WHICH I HAVE PRETTY WELL
MANAGED TO TAKE CARE OF,

08:12.459 --> 08:15.763
BECAUSE PEOPLE HAVE BEEN VERY
UNDERSTANDING OF OUR SITUATION.

08:15.763 --> 08:17.665
MR. BIDERMAN AT THE OFFICE
IS A VERY GOOD EXAMPLE,

08:17.665 --> 08:21.168
BUT IT HAS NOT BEEN EASY.
YOU GET THAT?

08:21.168 --> 08:22.435
SO, LET ME PUT IT THIS WAY--

08:22.435 --> 08:25.539
YOUR FATHER NEVER MET AN INSIDE
STRAIGHT HE DIDN'T LIKE.

08:25.539 --> 08:27.608
WHAT'S AN
INSIDE STRAIGHT?

08:27.608 --> 08:29.309
NEVER YOU MIND, BOBBY-O.

08:29.309 --> 08:32.111
DON'T YOU EVER LET ME CATCH YOU
PLAYING CARDS FOR MONEY.

08:32.111 --> 08:35.414
HAD ENOUGH OF THAT
TO LAST ME A LIFETIME.

08:35.414 --> 08:38.251
COME ON, THEN!

08:39.285 --> 08:42.990
HAT MUST BE THE NEW TENANT
FOR THE UPSTAIRS APARTMENT.

08:42.990 --> 08:46.493
I DON'T TRUST PEOPLE WHO MOVE
THEIR THINGS IN PAPER BAGS.

08:46.493 --> 08:48.195
THAT'S SO SLUTTY.

08:48.195 --> 08:50.163
WELL, HE HAS SUITCASES.

08:50.163 --> 08:51.965
YES, BUT THEY DON'T
MATCH, DO THEY?

08:51.965 --> 08:55.035
OH, HELLO, FOLKS.
I'M TED BRAUTIGAN.

08:55.035 --> 08:56.737
I'LL BE LIVING UPSTAIRS
FOR A WHILE. MA'AM.

08:56.737 --> 08:58.071
HOW DO YOU DO?

08:58.071 --> 09:00.574
I'M ELIZABETH GARFIELD
AND THIS IS MY SON ROBERT,

09:00.574 --> 09:02.142
AND IT'S VERY NICE
TO MEET YOU, MR. BRATTIGAN,

09:02.142 --> 09:03.777
BUT TEMPUS FUGIT.

09:03.777 --> 09:04.812
IT'S BRAUTIGAN,
MA'AM,

09:04.812 --> 09:06.580
BUT TED WILL BE
FINE WITH ME.

09:06.580 --> 09:08.448
Bobby: IT'S NICE TO
MEET YOU, MR. BRAUTIGAN.

09:08.448 --> 09:09.482
GO ON NOW.

09:09.482 --> 09:10.718
I HOPE YOU'LL
LIKE IT HERE.

09:10.718 --> 09:12.319
BOBBY!
THANK YOU, ROBERT.

09:14.254 --> 09:15.288
YEAH.

09:16.757 --> 09:18.892
Carol:
BIRTHDAY BOY! MWAH!

09:18.892 --> 09:20.594
CAROL, IT'S HARD
ENOUGH BEING FRIENDS

09:20.594 --> 09:22.796
WITHOUT YOU PULLING
STUFF LIKE THAT.

09:22.796 --> 09:25.498
YOU LOVED IT.
HERE.

09:25.498 --> 09:26.499
IS THIS GONNA BE GUSHY?

09:26.499 --> 09:27.735
I DON'T KNOW.

09:28.702 --> 09:30.337
BETTER NOT BE.

09:32.205 --> 09:34.307
OH.

09:34.307 --> 09:35.743
JUST LIKE IT, HUH?

09:35.743 --> 09:38.345
YEAH. THAT'S GREAT.
THANKS.

09:38.345 --> 09:39.346
SURE.

09:42.482 --> 09:43.951
DIDN'T GET THE BIKE,
DID YOU?

09:43.951 --> 09:46.754
NO BIG DEAL.
MOM CAN'T AFFORD IT.

09:46.754 --> 09:48.889
SHE BUYS HER
NEW DRESSES, THOUGH.

09:48.889 --> 09:51.524
SHE HAS TO LOOK NICE FOR
THE OFFICE, DOESN'T SHE?

09:51.524 --> 09:54.127
ARE YOU COMING?

09:54.127 --> 09:57.264
YEAH!
COME ON!

09:57.264 --> 09:59.967
[LAUGHING]
STOP! STOP!

10:01.268 --> 10:03.503
* COME ON, BABY *

10:03.503 --> 10:05.372
HEY, SULLY!
HEY!

10:05.372 --> 10:07.307
* DOO WOP WOP *

10:07.307 --> 10:09.643
* COME ON, BABY *

10:09.643 --> 10:10.644
DID YOU GET THE BIKE?

10:10.644 --> 10:11.645
NO.

10:11.645 --> 10:12.913
WELL, I GOT
NOTHIN' FOR YOU,

10:12.913 --> 10:15.515
BUT HAPPY BIRTHDAY
ANYWAY, YOU BASTARD!

10:15.515 --> 10:18.652
* AND GO LIKE THIS *

10:18.652 --> 10:21.521
* EE-OH, TWIST *

10:21.521 --> 10:22.522
COME ON!

10:22.522 --> 10:23.523
* BABY, TWIST *

10:23.523 --> 10:24.658
HANG ON!
WAIT FOR ME!

10:24.658 --> 10:28.796
* OOH, YEAH *

10:28.796 --> 10:30.397
* JUST LIKE THIS *

10:30.397 --> 10:31.498
* ROUND AND ROUND *

10:31.498 --> 10:34.634
* COME ON, LITTLE MISS *

10:34.634 --> 10:37.404
* AND DO THE TWIST *

10:37.404 --> 10:40.708
* MY DADDY IS SLEEPIN' *

10:40.708 --> 10:43.376
* AND MAMA AIN'T AROUND *

10:43.376 --> 10:44.444
* YEAH *

10:44.444 --> 10:46.479
[SLURPING]

10:46.479 --> 10:49.382
* AND MAMA AIN'T AROUND *

10:49.382 --> 10:52.419
* WE'RE GONNA
TWIST AND TWIST AND TWIST *

10:52.419 --> 10:53.854
WHAT'S AN
INSIDE STRAIGHT?

10:53.854 --> 10:56.389
SOMETHING TO DO
WITH GAMBLING, ISN'T IT?

10:56.389 --> 10:58.158
POKER. YOU TRY TO DRAW
A CARD IN THE MIDDLE.

10:58.158 --> 11:01.094
IT'S DUMB. STRICTLY
FOR SUCKERS. HEH HEH.

11:01.094 --> 11:01.929
[SLURPS]

11:01.929 --> 11:05.498
* OOH, YEAH *

11:05.498 --> 11:07.868
* JUST LIKE THIS *

11:07.868 --> 11:11.538
THIS NEIGHBORHOOD IS
GETTIN' TERRIBLY RUN DOWN.

11:11.538 --> 11:13.907
Bugs:
I THINK I'LL HAVE TO MOVE.

11:16.777 --> 11:19.747
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

11:19.747 --> 11:20.948
YEAH?

11:20.948 --> 11:22.750
Liz: OH, IS THAT HOW
WE ANSWER THE PHONE?

11:22.750 --> 11:25.085
OH, HI, MOM.
I'M SORRY.

11:25.085 --> 11:27.821
I WAS JUST EXCITED
ABOUT DINNER AND ALL.

11:27.821 --> 11:31.258
WELL, BOBBY,
MR. BIDERMAN IS SWAMPED

11:31.258 --> 11:32.192
AND HAS TO WORK LATE

11:32.192 --> 11:33.393
AND NEEDS ME
TO DO THE SAME,

11:33.393 --> 11:36.229
SO BIRTHDAY DINNER
AT THE COLONY IS OFF.

11:36.229 --> 11:37.264
Bobby: OH. OK, MOM.

11:37.264 --> 11:39.767
THERE ARE LEFTOVERS
IN THE FRIDGE

11:39.767 --> 11:41.802
AND I'LL BE HOME
TO TUCK YOU IN.

11:41.802 --> 11:44.805
OH, AND, BOBBY, MAKE SURE
TO TURN OFF THE GAS RING

11:44.805 --> 11:47.474
WHEN YOU'RE DONE WITH
THE STOVE, ALL RIGHTY?

11:47.474 --> 11:48.508
I KNOW.

11:48.508 --> 11:50.477
SEE YOU SOON.

11:59.386 --> 12:01.989
[TYPING]

12:07.828 --> 12:09.329
EVENING, ROBERT.

12:09.329 --> 12:10.130
HMM?

12:10.130 --> 12:11.731
OR SHOULD I SAY
BOBBY?

12:11.731 --> 12:15.235
OH, MR. BRAUTIGAN.
HI.

12:15.235 --> 12:18.038
IT'S TED.

12:18.038 --> 12:19.239
SORRY.

12:19.239 --> 12:23.443
TED'LL BE HARD FOR ME,
BUT I'LL TRY.

12:23.443 --> 12:26.013
YOU GOING OUT LATER?

12:26.013 --> 12:30.918
OH. I WAS SUPPOSED TO HAVE
A BIRTHDAY DINNER WITH MY MOM,

12:30.918 --> 12:33.620
BUT SHE HAD TO STAY AT WORK.

12:33.620 --> 12:35.488
EVEN THOUGH
SHE DIDN'T WANT TO.

12:37.424 --> 12:39.960
ARE YOU A RICH MAN, THEN?

12:39.960 --> 12:42.729
FROM YOUR BIRTHDAY GIFTS.

12:42.729 --> 12:46.900
OH. [SIGHS]

12:47.968 --> 12:50.603
JUST A LIBRARY CARD?

12:50.603 --> 12:53.773
AN ADULT LIBRARY CARD.
OH, MY.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.608
ALL THE MASTER
STORYTELLERS

12:55.608 --> 12:57.010
OF THE WORLD
JUST WAITING FOR YOU.

12:57.010 --> 13:01.581
YOU KNOW WHY SHE PICKED IT?
BECAUSE IT WAS FREE.

13:01.581 --> 13:03.383
AH, THAT DOESN'T MATTER.

13:03.383 --> 13:05.718
DON'T YOU GIVE UP
ON THIS CARD, BOBBY,

13:05.718 --> 13:08.188
'CAUSE BOOKS
CAN BE SOLID GOLD.

13:08.188 --> 13:10.657
THE GREAT ONES
HAVE BEEN GETTING US

13:10.657 --> 13:13.260
THROUGH THE NIGHTS
FOR CENTURIES NOW.

13:13.260 --> 13:15.595
JUST GIVE A WRITER
AN HOUR OR TWO TO HOOK YOU

13:15.595 --> 13:16.864
AND IF HE CAN'T,

13:16.864 --> 13:18.798
WISH HIM THE BEST
AND FIND SOMEONE ELSE.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.400
THINK YOU CAN TRY THAT?

13:20.400 --> 13:23.803
WELL, IF YOU DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING ELSE TO DO...

13:23.803 --> 13:26.573
WELL, FAIR ENOUGH.

13:26.573 --> 13:28.075
DON'T BE AFRAID.

13:28.075 --> 13:30.677
A TALE OF TWO CITIES
ENDS WITH A BEHEADING,

13:30.677 --> 13:32.145
ALL KINDS OF
GREAT STUFF.

13:32.145 --> 13:35.015
LOST HORIZON--
MAGIC IN PLACES UNKNOWN.

13:35.015 --> 13:37.517
CAN'T BEAT THAT.

13:37.517 --> 13:39.052
[TRAIN HORN BLOWS]

13:39.052 --> 13:43.490
WHERE'D YOU LIVE BEFORE
YOU CAME HERE, MR.--TED?

13:43.490 --> 13:47.394
SOME OTHER PLACE THAT
WASN'T AS NICE AS THIS.

13:47.394 --> 13:49.696
YOU, BOBBY, YOU
LIVED HERE LONG?

13:49.696 --> 13:53.666
YES, SIR.
SINCE MY DAD DIED.

13:53.666 --> 13:56.536
AH. WHEN WAS
THAT SAD DAY?

13:56.536 --> 13:57.871
WHEN I WAS 5.

13:57.871 --> 14:01.674
6 YEARS, HUH?

14:01.674 --> 14:04.377
I BET YOU KNOW EVERYTHING
THAT HAPPENS ON THIS STREET.

14:04.377 --> 14:06.513
SURE DO...

14:06.513 --> 14:10.483
BECAUSE NOTHING HAPPENS
ON THIS STREET.

14:10.483 --> 14:11.985
OH.

14:13.453 --> 14:15.588
[SIGHS] 6 YEARS.

14:15.588 --> 14:17.457
AH, THAT'S JUST A BLINK.

14:17.457 --> 14:18.725
SOME DAY YOU'LL AGREE.

14:18.725 --> 14:24.831
YOU KNOW, BEN JONSON CALLED
TIME "THE OLD BALD CHEATER."

14:24.831 --> 14:26.599
WHAT?

14:26.599 --> 14:31.504
BEN JONSON CALLED TIME
THE "OLD BALD CHEATER."

14:31.504 --> 14:32.805
I LIKE THAT.

14:32.805 --> 14:35.075
I THINK I DO, TOO.

14:35.075 --> 14:37.277
WHO'S BEN JONSON?

14:37.277 --> 14:40.880
HE WAS AN ENGLISH WRITER.
DEAD THESE MANY YEARS.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.683
BRILLIANT, BUT FOOLISH
ABOUT MONEY.

14:43.683 --> 14:47.587
AND...GIVEN TO FLATULENCE.

14:47.587 --> 14:49.489
WHAT'S FLATULENCE?

14:51.791 --> 14:54.627
[FARTING NOISE]

14:54.627 --> 14:58.131
[GIGGLES]

14:58.131 --> 15:01.201
YEAH. KIDS ALWAYS THINK
FARTS ARE FUNNY.

15:04.104 --> 15:06.139
MIGHT HAVE A JOB
FOR YOU LATER.

15:06.139 --> 15:08.775
HAVE TO THINK ABOUT IT
FIRST, THOUGH.

15:08.775 --> 15:09.876
REALLY?

15:09.876 --> 15:11.444
YEAH.

15:11.444 --> 15:14.447
IF IT WORKS OUT,
YOU MIGHT GET THAT BIKE.

15:17.985 --> 15:20.087
HOW'D YOU KNOW
I WANTED A BIKE?

15:20.087 --> 15:24.057
ALL KIDS WANT BIKES.

15:24.057 --> 15:26.259
[DOOR CLOSES]

15:31.164 --> 15:36.369
* ONLY YOU *

15:36.369 --> 15:42.542
* CAN MAKE THIS WORLD
SEEM RIGHT *

15:42.542 --> 15:47.847
* ONLY YOU *

15:47.847 --> 15:49.949
* CAN MAKE *

15:49.949 --> 15:54.254
* THE DARKNESS BRIGHT *

15:54.254 --> 15:56.823
HEY, MOM, I TOOK
ANOTHER LOOK AT THAT BIKE.

15:56.823 --> 15:57.824
MM-HMM?

15:57.824 --> 16:00.827
IT'S A PHANTOM,
26-INCHER,

16:00.827 --> 16:02.562
REAL SWELL.

16:02.562 --> 16:06.266
NO, PERFECT.
PERFECT IS MORE LIKE IT.

16:06.266 --> 16:08.435
WELL, START SAVING
THOSE PENNIES.

16:08.435 --> 16:10.137
[KNOCKING]

16:10.137 --> 16:13.106
TED? IT'S ME.

16:13.106 --> 16:14.507
HI, KIDDO. COME IN.

16:14.507 --> 16:17.510
THANKS FOR MAKING
THE SKYWARD JOURNEY.

16:17.510 --> 16:20.247
AN ICY ROOT BEER
AWAITS YOU AS A REWARD.

16:20.247 --> 16:23.516
COLDER THE BETTER.

16:23.516 --> 16:27.987
ONE FEELS THEM FIRST AT
THE BACK OF ONE'S EYES.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.589
FEELS WHAT?

16:31.591 --> 16:35.462
ONE FEELS THEM FIRST AT
THE BACK OF ONE'S EYES.

16:41.334 --> 16:42.769
YEAH.

16:44.971 --> 16:46.739
HEY, I DID LIKE YOU SAID.

16:46.739 --> 16:47.740
WHAT?

16:47.740 --> 16:49.476
I GAVE HIM
A COUPLE OF HOURS.

16:49.476 --> 16:52.779
OH, YEAH. LOST HORIZON.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

16:52.779 --> 16:54.747
BETTER THAN
THE HARDY BOYS.

16:54.747 --> 16:56.283
YEAH, SURE IS.

16:59.752 --> 17:02.155
TELL ME, BOBBY...

17:02.155 --> 17:04.723
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO MAKE A DOLLAR A WEEK?

17:04.723 --> 17:06.193
WOULD I EVER!

17:06.193 --> 17:07.460
WELL, THE TRUTH IS,

17:07.460 --> 17:09.362
MY EYES ARE BEGINNING
TO FAIL ME,

17:09.362 --> 17:14.166
AND IF YOU WILL READ ME
THE HARWICH JOURNAL EVERY DAY,

17:14.166 --> 17:17.569
HEADLINE STUFF, SPORTS,
COMICS, WANT ADS,

17:17.569 --> 17:21.241
I'LL GIVE YOU SAID DOLLAR.
WHAT DO YOU SAY, KIDDO?

17:21.241 --> 17:23.776
[DRINKING ROOT BEER]

17:23.776 --> 17:24.644
WHAT ELSE?

17:24.644 --> 17:26.479
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

17:26.479 --> 17:30.783
THERE'S GOT TO BE MORE
TO IT THAN THAT.

17:30.783 --> 17:33.086
YEAH, THERE IS.

17:33.086 --> 17:37.324
SO WHAT'S THE REAL JOB?

17:37.324 --> 17:39.792
I WANT YOU TO KEEP YOUR
EYES OPEN, THAT'S ALL.

17:39.792 --> 17:41.428
FOR WHAT?

17:41.428 --> 17:42.662
LOW MEN.

17:44.297 --> 17:46.699
THAT'S RIGHT, BOBBY.

17:46.699 --> 17:50.637
I USE THE TERM "LOW"
IN THE DICKENSIAN SENSE,

17:50.637 --> 17:53.606
MEANING "DANGEROUS"--
FELLOWS WHO ARE RUTHLESS

17:53.606 --> 17:56.443
AND STOP AT NOTHING
TO GET WHAT THEY WANT.

17:56.443 --> 17:59.779
YOUR REAL JOB
WILL SIMPLY BE TO...

17:59.779 --> 18:02.382
WALK AROUND THE AREA...

18:02.382 --> 18:03.783
AND IF YOU SEE THEM

18:03.783 --> 18:06.286
OR FIND EVIDENCE
THAT THEY'VE BEEN HERE,

18:06.286 --> 18:08.521
YOU WILL ALERT ME
IMMEDIATELY, OK?

18:08.521 --> 18:09.656
OK.

18:09.656 --> 18:12.459
AND WHY ARE THEY
HOT ON YOUR TRAIL?

18:14.694 --> 18:16.363
[EXHALES]

18:16.363 --> 18:19.166
A CERTAIN SOMETHING
I HAPPEN TO HAVE.

18:19.166 --> 18:21.000
LET'S LEAVE IT AT THAT.

18:21.000 --> 18:23.002
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

18:23.002 --> 18:24.837
SO WHAT DO THEY
LOOK LIKE?

18:24.837 --> 18:26.606
HMM?

18:26.606 --> 18:30.543
WELL, THEY WEAR
DARK CLOTHES, DARK HATS.

18:32.412 --> 18:34.581
THEY'RE KIND OF ANONYMOUS,

18:34.581 --> 18:38.218
BUT YOU CAN RECOGNIZE THEM
BY THE CARS THEY DRIVE--

18:38.218 --> 18:41.654
LOUD AND FLASHY.

18:41.654 --> 18:44.391
WHEN THEY MOVE,
THEY MOVE IN PACKS,

18:44.391 --> 18:47.794
LIKE ANIMALS CLOSING IN
ON THE KILL.

18:47.794 --> 18:50.797
AND, UH...

18:50.797 --> 18:53.500
THEY CAST LONG SHADOWS.

18:56.269 --> 18:58.871
AH, WHAT A WORLD.
[EXHALES]

19:02.409 --> 19:05.878
THEY'RE NOT COPS,
ARE THEY?

19:05.878 --> 19:09.249
OR SECRET AGENTS?

19:09.249 --> 19:12.919
ARE YOU ASKING
IF I'M A BAD GUY

19:12.919 --> 19:14.787
OR A COMMIE SPY?

19:14.787 --> 19:17.690
IT'S TRUE, I'VE SCAMPED
MY SHARE OF FINES,

19:17.690 --> 19:20.827
AND IF THERE WERE
LIBRARY POLICE,

19:20.827 --> 19:23.563
I'D BE ONE OF THEIR
"TEN MOST WANTED,"

19:23.563 --> 19:27.234
BUT, NO,
I NEVER ROBBED A BANK

19:27.234 --> 19:29.936
OR STOLE
A MILITARY SECRET.

19:29.936 --> 19:31.170
SO WHO ARE THEY?

19:31.170 --> 19:32.805
HMM?

19:32.805 --> 19:36.008
THEY'RE THUGS, BULLIES,
CALL THEM WHAT YOU WILL.

19:36.008 --> 19:37.210
THEY'RE BULLDOGS.

19:37.210 --> 19:39.145
RELENTLESS WHEN
THEY'RE AFTER SOMETHING.

19:39.145 --> 19:40.146
LIKE THIS SOMETHING
YOU HAVE?

19:40.146 --> 19:41.648
THAT'S RIGHT.

19:43.416 --> 19:47.454
AND WHAT THEY WANT IS ME
BACK UNDER THEIR CONTROL.

19:47.454 --> 19:48.621
SO YOU BE ON
THE LOOKOUT FOR THEM,

19:48.621 --> 19:50.390
BECAUSE WHEN
THEY'RE CLOSING IN,

19:50.390 --> 19:54.461
THEY LEAVE
STRANGE SIGNS IN CODE

19:54.461 --> 19:58.365
IN OBVIOUS PLACES
LIKE TELEPHONE POLES--

19:58.365 --> 20:01.734
POSTERS AND NOTICES FOR
LOST PETS AND LOST DOGS.

20:04.337 --> 20:06.306
NOW, IF I KNEW
WHAT THEY MIGHT DO,

20:06.306 --> 20:08.475
THEY'D NEVER CATCH ME,
BUT I DON'T.

20:08.475 --> 20:09.976
WHAT DO I DO
IF I SEE THEM?

20:09.976 --> 20:13.480
RUN LIKE HELL WAS AFTER YOU
AND TELL ME WHAT YOU'VE SEEN.

20:13.480 --> 20:15.014
YOU REMEMBER
WHEN WE MET A WEEK AGO

20:15.014 --> 20:17.517
AND I ASKED YOU IF YOU KNEW
WHAT WAS GOING ON AROUND HERE?

20:17.517 --> 20:19.352
SURE.

20:19.352 --> 20:22.555
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE
MY MAN, KIDDO.

20:28.961 --> 20:30.697
DON'T WORRY, TED.

20:30.697 --> 20:33.232
I WON'T LET
THE BOGEYMEN GET YOU.

20:33.232 --> 20:34.367
Liz: BOBBY?
ARE YOU UP THERE?

20:34.367 --> 20:35.668
DON'T WORRY.

20:35.668 --> 20:37.003
SHE CAN'T POSSIBLY KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

20:37.003 --> 20:38.605
YOU THINK SHE CAN AND
THAT'S HER POWER OVER YOU.

20:38.605 --> 20:40.373
THAT'S A MOTHER'S POWER.

20:40.373 --> 20:42.275
[LIZ KNOCKING]

20:42.275 --> 20:45.678
MRS. GARFIELD.

20:47.380 --> 20:50.383
WELL, IT'S VERY COZY
IN HERE.

20:50.383 --> 20:53.853
OH, MOM, TED--
I MEAN, MR. BRAUTIGAN,

20:53.853 --> 20:55.588
HE'S GONNA PAY ME
A DOLLAR A WEEK

20:55.588 --> 20:58.425
JUST TO READ HIM
THE PAPERS EVERY DAY.

20:58.425 --> 21:01.093
WELL, THAT'S
VERY GENEROUS.

21:01.093 --> 21:03.095
DO YOU ALWAYS HAVE
YOUNG BOYS

21:03.095 --> 21:05.264
READ YOU THE PAPERS,
MR. BRATTIGAN?

21:05.264 --> 21:07.233
IT'S BRAUTIGAN, MA'AM,

21:07.233 --> 21:10.102
AND, YES,
I NEED SOMEONE TO DO IT.

21:10.102 --> 21:13.239
MY EYES AREN'T WHAT THEY USED
TO BE SINCE I RETIRED.

21:13.239 --> 21:16.343
AND WHAT DID YOU DO
BEFORE THAT?

21:16.343 --> 21:19.779
I WORKED UP NORTH.
VARIOUS PLACES.

21:24.984 --> 21:26.386
WELL, COME ALONG, BOBBY.

21:26.386 --> 21:29.255
TIME AND TIDE
WAIT FOR NO MAN.

21:29.255 --> 21:31.824
BYE,
MR. BRAUTIGAN.

21:31.824 --> 21:33.059
BOBBY.

21:37.930 --> 21:39.599
[DOOR CLOSES]

21:42.702 --> 21:43.970
MOM, GUESS WHAT
MR. BRAUTIGAN--

21:43.970 --> 21:46.739
SHH, SHH, SHH.

21:46.739 --> 21:48.007
OK.

21:49.876 --> 21:51.911
SOMETHING DOESN'T
MAKE SENSE TO ME.

21:51.911 --> 21:52.945
WHAT?

21:52.945 --> 21:53.946
WHY WOULD A MAN HIS AGE

21:53.946 --> 21:56.182
WANT TO SPEND THAT MUCH
TIME WITH A KID?

21:56.182 --> 21:58.418
I DON'T KNOW...

21:58.418 --> 22:00.720
BUT WHAT I DO KNOW
IS THAT HE SAID

22:00.720 --> 22:03.423
I MUST BE SOME LUCKY KID
TO HAVE A MOM

22:03.423 --> 22:04.724
WHO WOULD ACTUALLY
LET ME HAVE

22:04.724 --> 22:08.395
A GROWN-UP LIBRARY CARD
FOR MY BIRTHDAY.

22:09.662 --> 22:12.164
[SIGHS]
I DON'T KNOW.

22:12.164 --> 22:13.400
I TRUST HIM
ABOUT AS FAR

22:13.400 --> 22:15.368
AS I COULD
SLING A PIANO.

22:15.368 --> 22:18.605
THAT'S RIGHT.
SPOIL IT FOR ME.

22:18.605 --> 22:21.441
YOU JUST NEVER WANT ME
TO GET THAT BIKE.

22:21.441 --> 22:23.209
I DO--I DO, AND
I WISH I COULD HAVE

22:23.209 --> 22:24.544
GOTTEN IT
FOR YOU MYSELF,

22:24.544 --> 22:26.045
BUT YOUR FATHER DIDN'T
EXACTLY LEAVE US

22:26.045 --> 22:27.346
WELL OFF, YOU KNOW.

22:27.346 --> 22:30.550
[SIGHS]
IT'S ONLY READING.

22:30.550 --> 22:32.752
[COME FLY WITH ME
PLAYING ON RECORD PLAYER]

22:34.821 --> 22:38.558
[SIGHS] ALL RIGHT.
WHAT'S THE HARM?

22:40.026 --> 22:41.127
YES, YES, YES, YES.

22:41.127 --> 22:45.398
BUT ONLY ON THE PORCH,
MIND, IN THE FRESH AIR.

22:45.398 --> 22:48.067
OK.

22:48.067 --> 22:50.069
* IF YOU CAN USE *

22:50.069 --> 22:51.438
* SOME EXOTIC BOOZE *

22:51.438 --> 22:54.306
[LOUDER] * THERE'S A BAR
IN FAR BOMBAY *

22:54.306 --> 22:55.675
* COME FLY WITH ME *

22:55.675 --> 22:59.211
* LET'S FLY, LET'S FLY AWAY *

22:59.211 --> 23:01.080
[LAUGHS]

23:01.080 --> 23:02.615
* COME FLY WITH ME *

23:02.615 --> 23:04.150
* LET'S FLOAT DOWN TO PERU *

23:04.150 --> 23:07.119
BYE, BOBBY.
BYE, CAROL.

23:07.119 --> 23:08.387
* IN LLAMA LAND... *

23:08.387 --> 23:10.590
SORRY, I'M LATE, TED.
I FORGOT THE TIME.

23:10.590 --> 23:12.191
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

23:12.191 --> 23:14.727
WE'RE ALL TIME'S CAPTIVES,

23:14.727 --> 23:16.796
HOSTAGES TO ETERNITY.

23:16.796 --> 23:17.930
BEN JONSON?

23:17.930 --> 23:20.299
NO. BORIS PASTERNAK.

23:20.299 --> 23:22.535
HE WAS A RUSSIAN...

23:22.535 --> 23:25.872
OF NO ACCOUNT, I THINK.

23:25.872 --> 23:27.574
SO WHAT'S GOING ON
IN THE BIG, WIDE WORLD?

23:27.574 --> 23:29.308
SOMETHING SCURRILOUS,
I SUPPOSE.

23:29.308 --> 23:31.811
"VICE PRESIDENT
RICHARD M. NIXON,

23:31.811 --> 23:34.514
"AFTER HAVING WON
THE REPUBLICAN NOMINATION

23:34.514 --> 23:36.348
"FOR PRESIDENT
ON THE FIRST BALLOT,

23:36.348 --> 23:39.752
CONFERS WITH
HENRY CABOT LODGE"--

23:39.752 --> 23:40.953
Carol: WE'RE GOIN'
FOR SOME ICE CREAM.

23:40.953 --> 23:41.788
YOU WANT TO COME?

23:41.788 --> 23:43.723
CAN'T. EARNING
MY DAILY BREAD.

23:45.291 --> 23:47.827
AFTERNOON,
MRS. GERBER, CAROL.

23:47.827 --> 23:49.061
HI, TED.

23:50.296 --> 23:52.899
I NEVER EVER SAW

23:52.899 --> 23:55.201
A GIRL AS SPECIAL
AS CAROL GERBER.

23:55.201 --> 23:57.904
THERE'S MILLIONS.

23:57.904 --> 24:00.306
OH, YEAH?

24:00.306 --> 24:01.774
HAVE YOU KISSED HER YET?

24:01.774 --> 24:03.409
YUCK.

24:03.409 --> 24:05.377
WELL, YOU WILL.
I PROMISE YOU.

24:05.377 --> 24:07.246
STAY AWAY.

24:07.246 --> 24:09.649
HA. YOU WILL,

24:09.649 --> 24:11.017
AND IT WILL BE THE KISS

24:11.017 --> 24:14.987
BY WHICH ALL OTHERS
IN YOUR LIFE WILL BE JUDGED...

24:14.987 --> 24:16.989
AND FOUND WANTING.

24:18.424 --> 24:20.593
ARE YOU DONE?

24:22.261 --> 24:24.664
YEAH. COME ON, READ TO ME.

24:24.664 --> 24:28.267
GO ON. COME BACK HERE
AND DO YOUR JOB.

24:28.267 --> 24:29.736
OK.

24:31.270 --> 24:34.140
BUT YOU WILL KISS HER.

24:34.140 --> 24:35.808
[SANTO & JOHNNY'S
SLEEP WALK PLAYING]

24:35.808 --> 24:38.010
[LAUGHTER AND YELLING]

24:46.418 --> 24:47.954
Carol: COME ON.

24:47.954 --> 24:49.355
[LAUGHING]

24:49.355 --> 24:51.724
NICE GOIN'.

24:58.297 --> 25:00.266
GET IN, PLEASE.

25:22.955 --> 25:25.257
[LAUGHING]

25:25.257 --> 25:27.426
Bobby:
HERE! GIMME IT!

25:27.426 --> 25:29.729
COME ON.
PLEASE?

25:29.729 --> 25:31.330
COME ON, SULLY.

25:31.330 --> 25:33.866
Carol: SULLY.

25:33.866 --> 25:36.268
Bobby: "F.B.I.
ANNOUNCES NEW MEASURES

25:36.268 --> 25:38.237
TO COMBAT
RED INFILTRATORS."

25:38.237 --> 25:41.173
HMPH.

25:41.173 --> 25:42.909
HEY, BOBBY.

25:42.909 --> 25:43.943
YEAH.

25:43.943 --> 25:45.244
WHEN YOU GET
TO FLASH GORDON,

25:45.244 --> 25:47.814
BE SURE AND TELL ME WHAT
DALE ARDEN'S WEARING.

25:47.814 --> 25:50.016
WHAT IS IT
WITH YOU AND HER?

25:50.016 --> 25:53.019
WELL, IF YOU MUST KNOW,
WHEN I WAS YOUNGER

25:53.019 --> 25:55.354
I THOUGHT SHE WAS
A REAL HOTSY-TOTSY.

25:55.354 --> 25:57.590
[CHUCKLES]

25:57.590 --> 26:01.060
OK, BEFORE COMICS,
WE'VE GOT SPORTS...

26:01.060 --> 26:03.095
BASEBALL. MMPH.

26:03.095 --> 26:06.332
"MAURY WILLS ON THE WAY
TO BREAK TY COBB'S RECORD."

26:06.332 --> 26:07.767
I SAW COBB.

26:07.767 --> 26:10.637
MY DAD SAW BABE RUTH.

26:10.637 --> 26:11.971
HE SAW HIM POINT
FOR THE HOME RUN...

26:11.971 --> 26:14.240
OH.
AGAINST THE CUBS.

26:14.240 --> 26:15.241
HE TOLD ME ALL ABOUT IT.

26:15.241 --> 26:19.078
HE TELL YOU OF NAGURSKI'S
COMEBACK GAME?

26:20.847 --> 26:23.115
I KNOW HE SAW IT, THOUGH.

26:23.115 --> 26:25.117
WERE YOU THERE?

26:25.117 --> 26:26.118
YEAH.

26:26.118 --> 26:29.155
YOU AND MY DAD
WERE AT THE SAME PLACE.

26:29.155 --> 26:31.958
YOU KNOW ABOUT
BRONKO NAGURSKI, HUH?

26:31.958 --> 26:34.694
HE WAS MY DAD'S HERO,
THAT'S ALL.

26:34.694 --> 26:37.864
THE GREATEST FOOTBALL
PLAYER THAT EVER LIVED.

26:37.864 --> 26:39.666
AFTER COLLEGE,
HE CAME TO CHICAGO,

26:39.666 --> 26:40.833
PLAYED 8 YEARS
FOR THE BEARS,

26:40.833 --> 26:43.235
MADE THEM CHAMPIONS,

26:43.235 --> 26:44.103
THEN HE RETIRED.

26:44.103 --> 26:46.739
WHEN HE WAS OLD,
6 YEARS RETIRED,

26:46.739 --> 26:48.908
THE BEARS BROUGHT HIM
BACK AS A SUBSTITUTE.

26:48.908 --> 26:50.677
LAST GAME OF THE SEASON,

26:50.677 --> 26:53.045
THEY WERE PLAYING
THE CROSSTOWN CARDINALS--

26:53.045 --> 26:55.648
SWORN ENEMIES.

26:55.648 --> 26:57.750
THE BEARS HAD TO BEAT
THE CARDINALS

26:57.750 --> 26:59.551
TO WIN THE CHAMPIONSHIP.

26:59.551 --> 27:02.021
NAGURSKI WASN'T
SUPPOSED TO PLAY,

27:02.021 --> 27:05.758
THIRD-STRING FULLBACK.
[CROWD CHEERING SOFTLY]

27:05.758 --> 27:09.195
THEN IN THE FIRST HALF,
THE STARTER WENT DOWN.

27:09.195 --> 27:11.263
THE SECOND HALF,
THERE WAS A PILE-UP.

27:11.263 --> 27:13.032
OH, NO.

27:13.032 --> 27:14.300
IF YOUR DAD WAS HERE
TELLING YOU THIS,

27:14.300 --> 27:16.803
HE WOULD HAVE SAID
HE WAS FRIGHTENED, BOBBY.

27:16.803 --> 27:18.671
HE WAS JUST SO SCARED.

27:18.671 --> 27:21.473
BUT WHY? NAGURSKI
WAS IN THE GAME.

27:21.473 --> 27:24.677
I WAS SCARED, TOO.
WE ALL WERE.

27:24.677 --> 27:26.578
SO WE WANTED A MIRACLE,
YOU SEE, BOBBY.

27:26.578 --> 27:29.749
WE--WE WANTED HIM
THE WAY HE WAS,

27:29.749 --> 27:32.251
THE OLD BRONKO NAGURSKI.

27:32.251 --> 27:33.986
WE WANTED HIM
THE WAY HE USED TO BE

27:33.986 --> 27:35.755
BACK IN THE OLD DAYS.

27:35.755 --> 27:37.924
DID HE DO GOOD, TED?

27:37.924 --> 27:40.860
'CAUSE I DON'T WANT
TO HEAR THIS IF HE DIDN'T.

27:43.730 --> 27:45.264
WELL, THE QUARTERBACK
GAVE HIM THE BALL,

27:45.264 --> 27:48.901
AND NAGURSKI RAN
SLOWLY UP TO THE LINE,

27:48.901 --> 27:52.739
AND THE CARDINALS
CRUSHED HIM,

27:52.739 --> 27:54.573
BUT SOMEHOW...

27:54.573 --> 27:56.542
[GAME CHATTER]

27:56.542 --> 28:00.046
SOMEHOW HE GAINED
A FEW YARDS.

28:00.046 --> 28:02.181
NEXT PLAY, THE SAME.
SAME THING PLAY AFTER THAT.

28:02.181 --> 28:05.351
THEY JUST KEPT GIVING
THE BALL TO THE OLD MAN,

28:05.351 --> 28:09.055
AND THE BEARS BEGAN
TO MOVE DOWN THE FIELD,

28:09.055 --> 28:11.690
5 YARDS, 10 YARDS...
[WHISTLE BLOWS FAINTLY]

28:11.690 --> 28:13.826
7 MORE.

28:13.826 --> 28:15.995
IF HE JUST COULD SCORE
FOR US, WE COULD WIN.

28:15.995 --> 28:20.767
WE COULD BE CHAMPIONS
AGAIN.

28:20.767 --> 28:24.303
GO ON, TED.
YOU CAN'T STOP.

28:27.573 --> 28:29.375
HUH.

28:29.375 --> 28:31.377
TED.

28:32.411 --> 28:35.714
COME ON. I'VE GOTTA
KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.

28:40.052 --> 28:41.420
COME ON.

28:41.420 --> 28:43.856
YOU KNOW WHAT YOUR DAD
DID RIGHT THEN, BOBBY?

28:43.856 --> 28:46.392
NO, NO, NO. YEAH.
WHAT DID MY FATHER DO?

28:46.392 --> 28:48.227
HE JUMPED TO HIS FEET.
HE WAS SCREAMING.

28:48.227 --> 28:49.829
WE ALL WERE BECAUSE
WE COULDN'T BELIEVE

28:49.829 --> 28:51.097
WHAT WAS HAPPENING
ON THE FIELD.

28:51.097 --> 28:53.866
OH, MY GOD,
WHAT WAS IT? GO ON.

28:53.866 --> 28:55.868
IT WAS OUR MIRACLE,
YOU SEE...

28:55.868 --> 28:57.003
[CROWD CHANTING]

28:57.003 --> 28:59.305
BECAUSE
HE WAS CRAWLING.

28:59.305 --> 29:03.075
BRONKO NAGURSKI WAS CRAWLING
TOWARD THE GOAL LINE,

29:03.075 --> 29:04.877
AND THEY JUST PILED
EVERYTHING ON HIM,

29:04.877 --> 29:06.645
DID EVERYTHING
THEY COULD TO STOP HIM.

29:06.645 --> 29:09.816
BUT NOTHING
COULD STOP HIM.

29:09.816 --> 29:12.985
YEAH,
THAT'S RIGHT, BOBBY,

29:12.985 --> 29:15.922
NOT ON THAT DAY,

29:15.922 --> 29:19.191
NOT WHEN YOUR DAD AND I
SAW THE MIRACLE,

29:19.191 --> 29:21.493
WHEN THE OLD MAN
BROUGHT US HOME.

29:21.493 --> 29:24.363
[CROWD CHEERING]

29:24.363 --> 29:25.364
HE SCORED.

29:25.364 --> 29:28.567
HE SCORED FOR US.

29:28.567 --> 29:30.036
Crowd:
NAGURSKI! NAGURSKI!

29:30.036 --> 29:32.371
WE WERE CHAMPIONS AGAIN.

29:32.371 --> 29:33.906
I JUST KNEW HE WOULD.

29:33.906 --> 29:35.808
[CROWD FADES]

29:38.744 --> 29:40.847
YEAH, THEN
HE WAS GONE AGAIN,

29:40.847 --> 29:44.450
BACK TO THE NORTH
WHERE HE CAME FROM.

29:44.450 --> 29:48.420
BRONKO NAGURSKI.
[DISTANT BELL CHIMING]

29:48.420 --> 29:51.290
Liz: BOBBY! BOBBY-O!

30:08.774 --> 30:10.342
TED.

30:10.342 --> 30:11.844
YEAH.

30:11.844 --> 30:15.414
WELL, I KNOW THE LOW MEN
DON'T EXIST,

30:15.414 --> 30:17.049
BUT IF A BUNCH OF 'EM

30:17.049 --> 30:18.517
STARTED DRIVING
AROUND HERE

30:18.517 --> 30:20.887
AND THE STRANGE SIGNS
STARTED APPEARING

30:20.887 --> 30:23.255
ON THE TELEPHONE POLES--

30:23.255 --> 30:27.426
WELL, WE BOTH KNOW
THAT COULDN'T HAPPEN,

30:27.426 --> 30:29.595
BUT IF IT DID...

30:39.972 --> 30:43.910
WOULD YOU HAVE
TO GO AWAY?

30:45.311 --> 30:48.714
YEAH. IT WOULDN'T BE SAFE
FOR ME HERE, KIDDO,

30:48.714 --> 30:52.318
AND WISHING CANNOT
MAKE IT SO.

30:52.318 --> 30:53.920
Liz: BOBBY!

31:01.860 --> 31:03.395
[DOOR CLOSES]

31:10.302 --> 31:13.605
BOBBY, THIS TED OF YOURS...

31:15.507 --> 31:17.709
DID HE TELL YOU
WHERE HE CAME FROM?

31:17.709 --> 31:20.646
EH. SOME PLACE
NOT AS NICE AS HERE

31:20.646 --> 31:22.348
I THINK HE SAID.

31:22.348 --> 31:24.450
AH.

31:24.450 --> 31:27.853
WELL, THAT DOESN'T
TELL US MUCH, DOES IT?

31:27.853 --> 31:28.854
MMM.

31:28.854 --> 31:31.557
ANYTHING ELSE?

31:31.557 --> 31:33.459
NOPE.

31:36.628 --> 31:38.197
BOBBY...

31:38.197 --> 31:40.299
HMM?

31:42.001 --> 31:44.870
DOES HE--

31:44.870 --> 31:47.039
WHAT?

31:51.277 --> 31:52.511
NOTHING.

31:52.511 --> 31:54.313
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

31:54.313 --> 31:55.547
JUST PROMISE ME
YOU'LL TELL ME

31:55.547 --> 31:57.916
IF ANYTHING UNUSUAL
HAPPENS, ALL RIGHT?

32:00.552 --> 32:02.388
HELLO?

32:02.388 --> 32:04.090
HI.

32:06.858 --> 32:08.694
YOU PROMISED.

32:08.694 --> 32:10.662
I REALLY NEED THE--

32:12.031 --> 32:13.032
[TELEPHONE HANGS UP]

32:13.032 --> 32:14.600
WHO WAS THAT?

32:14.600 --> 32:18.237
NOTHING, HONEY.
IT'S JUST A WRONG NUMBER.

32:23.709 --> 32:25.677
[DOOR SLAMS]

32:25.677 --> 32:26.945
Liz: SON OF A BITCH.

32:26.945 --> 32:29.148
[CRYING]

32:50.736 --> 32:52.071
I KNOW IT'S YOU, BOBBY.

32:52.071 --> 32:54.173
YOUR MOM SAYS
SHE'S ALMOST READY.

32:54.173 --> 32:55.841
GREAT! YOU THINK TED
WOULD LIKE TO COME?

32:55.841 --> 32:57.009
TO THE FAIR?

32:57.009 --> 32:58.677
DON'T YOU THINK
HE'D LIKE TO BE ASKED?

32:58.677 --> 33:00.112
I GUESS.

33:00.112 --> 33:02.848
YOU DO IT.
I'LL GO GET SULLY.

33:02.848 --> 33:04.116
OK.

33:05.984 --> 33:08.287
HEY, HOW DO YOU LIKE
BEING BEATEN BY A GIRL?

33:08.287 --> 33:10.522
[LAUGHS]
HEY, NO FAIR.

33:12.658 --> 33:14.260
[GROWLS]

33:23.169 --> 33:25.003
MR. BIDERMAN
NEEDS ME TO COME IN.

33:25.003 --> 33:26.305
ON A SATURDAY?

33:26.305 --> 33:28.474
WELL, SOME PEOPLE HAVE
TO WORK FOR THEIR MONEY.

33:28.474 --> 33:29.741
MOM.
WHAT?

33:29.741 --> 33:30.942
YOU PROMISED.

33:30.942 --> 33:32.978
OH, HONEY. THESE ARE
JUST KOOLS, BOBBY-O.

33:32.978 --> 33:34.213
READ THE ADVERTISING.

33:34.213 --> 33:36.215
KOOLS. THEY COOL
THE THROAT.

33:36.215 --> 33:38.650
THEY'RE HARDLY EVEN
CIGARETTES AT ALL.

33:38.650 --> 33:39.651
MOM?

33:39.651 --> 33:40.552
WHAT?

33:40.552 --> 33:41.653
COULD I PLEASE HAVE
A LITTLE MONEY

33:41.653 --> 33:42.454
FOR THE RIDES AND STUFF?

33:42.454 --> 33:44.156
OHH, YOU NEVER STOP,
DO YOU?

33:44.156 --> 33:46.292
HONEY, AREN'T YOU EARNING
YOUR OWN MONEY NOW?

33:46.292 --> 33:47.993
YEAH, BUT THAT'S
FOR THE BIKE.

33:47.993 --> 33:49.395
WELL, IF YOU WANT
TO SPEND IT

33:49.395 --> 33:51.263
RIDING THE LOOP-DE-LOOP
WITH YOUR LITTLE GIRLFRIEND

33:51.263 --> 33:53.031
THAT'S YOUR BUSINESS.

34:10.849 --> 34:12.217
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

34:12.217 --> 34:14.320
TED, IT'S ME.

34:14.320 --> 34:16.288
YOU WANT TO COME
TO THE FAIR?

34:19.690 --> 34:21.793
[KNOCKS]

34:21.793 --> 34:23.728
TED?

34:42.080 --> 34:43.949
IS EVERYTHING OK?

34:43.949 --> 34:46.152
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

34:53.859 --> 34:56.295
TED, WAKE UP.

34:59.498 --> 35:01.367
TED, YOU'VE
GOTTA HELP ME.

35:01.367 --> 35:04.670
TED, I DON'T
KNOW WHAT TO DO.

35:04.670 --> 35:08.174
THEY DRAW WEST NOW.

35:08.174 --> 35:10.309
WHO? JESUS, TED,
PLEASE.

35:10.309 --> 35:15.381
THEY DRAW WEST NOW,
BUT THEY MAY BE BACK.

35:20.085 --> 35:25.457
TED, PLEASE,
YOU CAN'T DIE ON ME.

35:25.457 --> 35:26.958
PLEASE.

35:26.958 --> 35:28.160
AAH!

35:29.961 --> 35:30.962
[SIGHS]

35:30.962 --> 35:33.131
OH, MY GOD.

35:33.131 --> 35:36.802
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

35:36.802 --> 35:38.537
[SIGHS]

35:40.472 --> 35:43.342
I WENT OFF AGAIN, DIDN'T I?

35:43.342 --> 35:45.177
YOU MEAN LIKE
AT THE FRIDGE?

35:45.177 --> 35:46.945
YEAH.

35:46.945 --> 35:49.748
NO. WAY WORSE.

35:51.317 --> 35:52.651
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
HAVING A FIT

35:52.651 --> 35:56.087
OR SOMETHING.

35:56.087 --> 35:57.356
NO, IT'S ALL RIGHT,
BOBBY.

35:57.356 --> 35:58.624
BUT IF IT HAPPENS AGAIN,

35:58.624 --> 36:00.526
IT'S BEST YOU
DIDN'T TOUCH ME.

36:00.526 --> 36:04.230
NOBODY SHOULD TOUCH ME,
THAT'S ALL.

36:04.230 --> 36:05.864
SORRY.

36:08.234 --> 36:10.902
IS IT SAFE
TO LEAVE YOU ALONE?

36:10.902 --> 36:11.903
YEAH.

36:15.106 --> 36:17.309
IT'S OK.

36:19.611 --> 36:21.947
[SIGHS] OK.

36:26.652 --> 36:30.389
UM, MRS. GERBER'S
TAKING US TO THE FAIR.

36:30.389 --> 36:33.492
CAROL AND I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT LIKE TO COME.

36:33.492 --> 36:35.827
THANK YOU, BOBBY,
BUT I THINK JUST NOW,

36:35.827 --> 36:39.197
UM, IT'S NOT WISE.

36:50.108 --> 36:52.578
THE CIGARETTES
ARE ON THE TABLE.

36:54.346 --> 36:57.316
THANKS, KIDDO.

36:57.316 --> 36:58.817
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

36:58.817 --> 37:02.153
YOU RUN ALONG NOW.
ENJOY YOURSELF.

37:02.153 --> 37:04.623
DON'T FALL OUT
OF ANYTHING.

37:14.900 --> 37:16.902
[CHILDREN SCREAMING]

37:19.204 --> 37:22.341
* OH, CAROL *

37:22.341 --> 37:25.277
* DON'T LET HIM STEAL
YOUR HEART AWAY *

37:26.578 --> 37:28.480
* I'M GONNA LEARN TO DANCE *

37:28.480 --> 37:30.916
* IF IT TAKES ME
ALL NIGHT AND DAY *

37:30.916 --> 37:32.150
[SCREAMING]

37:32.150 --> 37:35.921
* CLIMB INTO MY MACHINE
SO WE CAN CRUISE ON OUT *

37:38.256 --> 37:40.292
* I KNOW
A SWINGIN' LITTLE JOINT *

37:40.292 --> 37:42.961
* WHERE WE CAN
JUMP AND SHOUT *

37:44.430 --> 37:46.264
* IT'S NOT TOO FAR
BACK OFF THE HIGHWAY *

37:46.264 --> 37:48.133
* NOT TOO FAR OF A RIDE *

37:48.133 --> 37:49.134
NO!

37:49.134 --> 37:50.836
YES!

37:50.836 --> 37:52.103
YES! YES!

37:52.103 --> 37:53.739
Child: YAY!

37:53.739 --> 37:55.206
WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA NAME IT?

37:55.206 --> 37:56.207
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

37:56.207 --> 37:57.242
ALL RIGHT,

37:57.242 --> 37:59.911
STEP RIGHT UP,
STEP RIGHT UP.

37:59.911 --> 38:01.513
HEY, WHO FEELS LUCKY?

38:01.513 --> 38:03.449
FIND THE QUEEN
OF HEARTS

38:03.449 --> 38:05.417
AND WIN YOURSELF
ANOTHER DAY.

38:05.417 --> 38:07.586
HEY, EASY AS CAN BEEZY.

38:07.586 --> 38:09.154
EASY-PEEZY-JAPANEEZY.

38:09.154 --> 38:11.056
ALL YOU GOTTA DO IS

38:11.056 --> 38:12.358
FIND THE QUEEN
OF HEARTS.

38:12.358 --> 38:14.159
HERE, PUT DOWN
YOUR BET.

38:14.159 --> 38:15.160
I'LL DO IT AGAIN.

38:15.160 --> 38:16.161
JUST ONE QUARTER.

38:16.161 --> 38:17.262
ALL RIGHT,
ONE.

38:17.262 --> 38:19.631
SEE, A JACK.
WE GOT THE KING,

38:19.631 --> 38:21.400
AND WE GOT THE QUEEN.

38:21.400 --> 38:23.869
JUST TELL ME WHERE
THE LADY LANDS.

38:23.869 --> 38:25.771
HEH!
Crowd: AHH.

38:29.307 --> 38:30.776
FORTUNE AWAITS YOU.

38:30.776 --> 38:32.411
THAT ONE THERE.

38:33.479 --> 38:34.980
YES!
GENIUS.

38:38.216 --> 38:39.885
OK.

38:39.885 --> 38:41.319
Mrs. Gerber: OK.

38:41.319 --> 38:43.355
[MOVING CARDS]

38:50.328 --> 38:52.731
UM, THAT ONE THERE.

38:52.731 --> 38:53.532
OH.
OH.

38:53.532 --> 38:54.533
Dealer:
HEARTBREAK.

38:54.533 --> 38:55.901
OK, KIDS,
THAT'S ENOUGH.

38:55.901 --> 38:58.570
MRS. GERBER, I CAN BEAT HIM.
I CAN SPOT HIS MOVES.

38:58.570 --> 39:00.238
I MAY AS WELL
GIVE UP, THEN.

39:00.238 --> 39:01.239
JUST A QUARTER.
ONE.

39:01.239 --> 39:03.675
OK.
[LAUGHS]

39:04.776 --> 39:07.546
[SING-SONG]
UP AND DOWN, ALL AROUND,

39:07.546 --> 39:09.848
IN AND OUT,
ALL ABOUT.

39:09.848 --> 39:14.753
NOW THEY'RE BACK,
SIDE BY SIDE.

39:14.753 --> 39:17.956
TELL ME, MISTER,
WHERE DOES SHE HIDE?

39:18.824 --> 39:20.258
IT'S THE ONE
ON THE RIGHT.

39:20.258 --> 39:21.660
Sully:
NO, NO, NO, NO.

39:21.660 --> 39:22.728
IT'S THE ONE ON
THE LEFT RIGHT THERE.

39:22.728 --> 39:24.596
THAT'S MY BABY,
RIGHT THERE.

39:25.464 --> 39:26.598
All: OHH.

39:26.598 --> 39:29.034
OK, GANG,
THAT'S ENOUGH.

39:29.034 --> 39:30.436
HEY, BOBBY WAS RIGHT.

39:30.436 --> 39:31.503
Dealer: A PRODIGY
WALKS AMONGST US.

39:31.503 --> 39:32.471
HEY, WHY DON'T YOU
WIN EVERYBODY

39:32.471 --> 39:33.472
THEIR MONEY BACK?

39:33.472 --> 39:34.573
UH, YOU KNOW,
I COULD,

39:34.573 --> 39:35.974
BUT I'M NOT SUPPOSED
TO PLAY CARDS

39:35.974 --> 39:37.075
FOR MONEY, SO--

39:37.075 --> 39:38.076
A BOASTY BOY.

39:38.076 --> 39:39.310
HE SAYS HE CAN WIN,
BUT HE'S TOO AFRAID

39:39.310 --> 39:40.612
TO BACK UP HIS BOAST.

39:40.612 --> 39:42.481
BOBBY, I COULD HAVE
MY MONEY BACK.

39:42.481 --> 39:44.215
COME ON.
BEAT HIM FOR ME.

39:44.215 --> 39:45.350
UH--
COME ON!

39:45.350 --> 39:46.418
Mrs. Gerber:
I DON'T THINK

39:46.418 --> 39:47.486
I CAN LET YOU
DO THIS, SWEETIE.

39:47.486 --> 39:49.220
YOUR MOTHER WOULD
NOT BE HAPPY.

39:49.220 --> 39:51.122
MY MOM'S
NEVER HAPPY.

39:51.122 --> 39:53.191
OK. IT'S ALL
I GOT.

39:53.191 --> 39:54.793
THIS IS THE MOVE
THAT STUNNED

39:54.793 --> 39:58.129
THE SHEIK OF ARABY.
BEHOLD.

40:06.905 --> 40:09.708
THIS ONE RIGHT HERE,
IN THE MIDDLE.

40:14.245 --> 40:16.114
OH! THAT'S IT!

40:16.114 --> 40:17.483
Sully:
ALL RIGHT, BOBBY!

40:19.651 --> 40:21.319
IT WAS JUST A LUCKY
GUESS, MISTER.

40:21.319 --> 40:22.588
WHY DON'T YOU
DOUBLE YOUR BET?

40:22.588 --> 40:25.256
THAT WAY EVERYBODY
CAN GO HOME HAPPY.

40:25.256 --> 40:27.793
FINE.

40:34.666 --> 40:37.503
THIS NEXT ONE IS
5 YEARS OF MY LIFE.

40:50.616 --> 40:52.818
[CARDS ECHOING]

41:18.043 --> 41:19.611
THIS ONE HERE.

41:22.313 --> 41:24.650
NOBODY EVER BEAT
THAT SHUFFLE.

41:27.418 --> 41:29.921
WELL, MISTER,
IS IT OR ISN'T IT?

41:32.724 --> 41:34.726
[GASPS] YES!
THAT'S THE ONE.

41:34.726 --> 41:35.727
Sully:
ALL RIGHT, BOBBY!

41:35.727 --> 41:37.262
IT WAS A FLUKE.

41:37.262 --> 41:39.230
YOU BET IT WAS
A FLUKE.

41:43.501 --> 41:45.136
NOW BEAT IT, KID.

41:45.136 --> 41:45.937
OK, GANG, LET'S GO.

41:45.937 --> 41:47.606
THAT'S ENOUGH.
LET'S GO.

41:47.606 --> 41:49.074
COME ON, BOBBY.

41:51.476 --> 41:54.145
STEP RIGHT UP!
WE HAD A WINNER HERE.

41:54.145 --> 41:58.049
IT'S EASY AS CAN BEEZY.
EASY-PEEZY-JAPANEEZY!

42:05.691 --> 42:07.025
Bobby:
YES, YES, YES!

42:18.036 --> 42:19.537
DON'T BE AFRAID.

42:19.537 --> 42:21.873
WHEN WE SWUNG OUT,
I-I WAS AFRAID

42:21.873 --> 42:24.309
WE WERE COMING LOOSE
AND FALLING TO OUR DOOM.

42:24.309 --> 42:27.178
WE'RE AS SAFE
AS CAN BE.

42:31.382 --> 42:34.019
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING?

42:34.019 --> 42:37.555
WELL, I THOUGHT
YOU WANTED ME TO.

42:37.555 --> 42:41.593
I JUST WASN'T READY,
THAT'S ALL.

42:41.593 --> 42:43.995
OK.

42:46.564 --> 42:48.466
BOBBY, DO IT AGAIN.

42:48.466 --> 42:50.736
I-I BETTER NOT.
YOU'LL TELL.

42:50.736 --> 42:53.038
AH, NO, IT'LL BE
OUR SECRET.

42:53.038 --> 42:55.206
HURRY, BEFORE
WE GO DOWN.

42:58.744 --> 43:02.213
BOBBY, I'M DYING HERE.

43:14.993 --> 43:16.227
[GIGGLES]

43:22.567 --> 43:23.702
THANK YOU, BOBBY.

43:23.702 --> 43:25.971
THAT WAS JUST
THE NICEST THING.

43:26.805 --> 43:29.374
AND IT'LL BE THE KISS
BY WHICH ALL OTHERS

43:29.374 --> 43:31.176
IN OUR LIFE
WILL BE JUDGED.

43:31.176 --> 43:32.477
WHAT?

43:32.477 --> 43:33.845
I DON'T KNOW.

43:33.845 --> 43:35.914
SOUNDED BETTER
WHEN TED SAID IT.

43:55.366 --> 43:56.367
[PLAYING HARMONICA]

43:56.367 --> 43:57.836
Carol: YOU KNEW,
DIDN'T YOU?

43:57.836 --> 44:00.638
WHERE THE QUEEN
OF HEARTS WAS?

44:00.638 --> 44:01.773
Bobby: YEAH.

44:01.773 --> 44:03.608
IT WAS LIKE I COULD
TELL EVERYTHING

44:03.608 --> 44:05.176
THAT WAS GOING ON
IN HIS HEAD.

44:05.176 --> 44:08.546
SO, EVERY THOUGHT
HE HAD, I KNEW IT,

44:08.546 --> 44:09.815
AND HE COULDN'T
FOOL ME.

44:09.815 --> 44:10.882
CAN YOU TELL
WHAT'S GOING ON

44:10.882 --> 44:12.183
IN SULLY'S HEAD?

44:14.052 --> 44:16.487
NAH, SULLY'S HEAD
IS ALWAYS EMPTY.

44:16.487 --> 44:19.590
OH YEAH? MAYBE
I'M THINKING OF...

44:19.590 --> 44:20.926
GETTING A NEW GLOVE
FOR NEXT YEAR.

44:20.926 --> 44:24.395
YOU ARE? WELL--WELL,
WHAT ABOUT THAT ONE?

44:24.395 --> 44:26.264
YOU REALLY WANT IT?

44:26.264 --> 44:28.233
ARE YOU KIDDING?
I LOVE THAT GLOVE!

44:28.233 --> 44:31.602
THEN, BOBBY GARFIELD,
IT IS YOURS.

44:31.602 --> 44:33.238
I'LL LEAVE IT TO YOU
IN MY WILL.

44:35.173 --> 44:37.743
SULLY, YOU JUST
LOVE DOING THAT.

44:37.743 --> 44:39.677
[LAUGHING]
I GOT YOU AGAIN.

44:39.677 --> 44:41.947
Bobby: WAIT,
NO, NO, NO, NO!

44:41.947 --> 44:43.581
YOU KNOW,
WHEN YOU'RE YOUNG,

44:43.581 --> 44:47.385
YOU HAVE MOMENTS
OF SUCH HAPPINESS.

44:47.385 --> 44:52.457
YOU THINK YOU'RE LIVING
IN SOMEPLACE MAGICAL,

44:52.457 --> 44:53.725
LIKE ATLANTIS
MUST HAVE BEEN.

44:53.725 --> 44:55.526
Bobby:
OH, HEY, CAROL,

44:55.526 --> 44:57.595
I OWE YOU $75
AND IT'S YOUR TURN.

44:57.595 --> 44:59.264
OK.

45:01.066 --> 45:03.034
HERE, GIVE ME
25 BACK.

45:03.034 --> 45:03.869
25?

45:03.869 --> 45:07.472
[ALL TALKING]

45:07.472 --> 45:10.441
[LAUGHING]

45:10.441 --> 45:12.477
Ted: THEN WE GROW UP...

45:14.079 --> 45:17.248
AND OUR HEARTS
BREAK IN TWO.

45:22.220 --> 45:24.355
[PLAYING]

45:31.429 --> 45:33.431
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

45:38.369 --> 45:39.370
COME ON.

45:39.370 --> 45:41.039
HANG ON.

45:43.641 --> 45:45.977
WHAT IS IT?

45:49.714 --> 45:51.716
I WONDER WHAT IT MEANS,
DON'T YOU?

45:51.716 --> 45:52.951
IT MEANS SOMEBODY

45:52.951 --> 45:55.753
LOST THEIR PET,
GOOFBALL. COME ON.

45:56.922 --> 45:58.223
WELL, YEAH,
BUT MAYBE

45:58.223 --> 45:59.757
IT'S A SECRET CODE
FOR SOMETHING.

45:59.757 --> 46:01.059
A SECRET CODE?

46:01.059 --> 46:02.160
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

46:02.160 --> 46:03.428
Harry: HEY, FAIRY!
I'LL TAKE THAT!

46:03.428 --> 46:04.629
I'M NOT
A FAIRY!

46:04.629 --> 46:05.931
DON'T TALK
TO THEM!

46:05.931 --> 46:07.933
HOW ARE YOUR TITS
COMING, GERBER BABY?

46:07.933 --> 46:09.134
Carol: GO AWAY!

46:09.134 --> 46:09.968
WHOO-HOO!

46:09.968 --> 46:12.437
Bobby: SHUT UP,
HARRY DOOLIN!

46:12.437 --> 46:14.439
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

46:20.711 --> 46:24.715
[GUNSHOTS ON TV]

46:24.715 --> 46:25.917
Lone Ranger:
HI YO, SILVER!

46:25.917 --> 46:27.685
Liz: BOBBY-O,
HOW WAS SCHOOL?

46:27.685 --> 46:28.920
GOOD.

46:28.920 --> 46:31.823
YOU WILL NEVER GUESS.
DON--MR. BIDERMAN--

46:31.823 --> 46:34.225
HAS INVITED ME
TO A SEMINAR

46:34.225 --> 46:36.061
ON THE WEEKEND
IN PROVIDENCE.

46:36.061 --> 46:37.829
"REAL ESTATE
IN THE SIXTIES."

46:37.829 --> 46:39.764
MR. CUSHMAN AND MR. DEAN
ARE GOING TOO,

46:39.764 --> 46:42.968
BUT I WAS AMAZED
THAT HE ASKED ME.

46:44.602 --> 46:46.404
BOBBY.

46:46.404 --> 46:49.574
BOBBY, I'VE WANTED TO BE
AN AGENT FOR SO LONG.

46:49.574 --> 46:50.942
THIS IS
A BIG CHANCE FOR ME.

46:50.942 --> 46:52.844
GREAT. WHEN IS IT?

46:52.844 --> 46:54.980
FRIDAY AFTERNOON.
NOW, IT'S JUST FOR 2 NIGHTS.

46:54.980 --> 46:56.848
NOW, I CAN'T
HAVE YOU STAYING

46:56.848 --> 46:58.016
AT YOUR LITTLE
GIRLFRIEND'S HOUSE.

46:58.016 --> 46:59.184
SHE'S NOT
MY GIRLFRIEND.

46:59.184 --> 47:00.718
WHATEVER.
I CAN'T HAVE YOU

47:00.718 --> 47:02.120
STAYING THERE
FOR OBVIOUS REASONS,

47:02.120 --> 47:04.389
SO I'M GONNA ASK
SULLY-JOHN'S MOTHER

47:04.389 --> 47:05.723
TO PUT YOU UP.

47:05.723 --> 47:07.025
THAT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

47:07.025 --> 47:09.627
BUT...IT HAS TO.

47:09.627 --> 47:12.597
THEY'RE GONNA VISIT
HIS GRANDMA.

47:12.597 --> 47:14.599
[SIGHS]
JUST MY LUCK.

47:14.599 --> 47:16.334
JUST MY ROTTEN LUCK.

47:16.334 --> 47:18.336
[FOOTSTEPS]

47:22.073 --> 47:24.442
BOBBY, WHY DON'T YOU
ASK YOUR FRIEND

47:24.442 --> 47:28.179
TO COME DOWN FOR
A NICE CUP OF TEA?

47:28.179 --> 47:29.447
OK.

47:36.621 --> 47:37.989
I'M SORRY,
MRS. GARFIELD,

47:37.989 --> 47:39.657
BUT, UH, NO.

47:39.657 --> 47:40.791
I-I WOULDN'T
BE MUCH

47:40.791 --> 47:42.928
OF A BABY-SITTER
FOR BOBBY.

47:42.928 --> 47:44.963
BUT I'VE NEVER
BEEN INVITED

47:44.963 --> 47:47.432
TO A REAL SEMINAR
BEFORE.

47:47.432 --> 47:49.734
YOU COULD SLEEP
ON THE PULL-OUT COUCH,

47:49.734 --> 47:51.069
WHICH IS OH,
SO COMFORTABLE,

47:51.069 --> 47:52.737
AND YOU TWO COULD GO
TO THE DINER,

47:52.737 --> 47:56.007
AND THEN MAYBE EVEN
TAKE IN A MOVIE.

47:56.007 --> 47:58.643
WELL, I'LL
TELL YOU WHAT.

47:58.643 --> 48:00.878
IF BOBBY WANTS
ME TO, I WILL.

48:04.349 --> 48:06.151
Liz: BOBBY?

48:07.418 --> 48:10.421
WELL, HOW COME YOU GET
TO HAVE ALL THE FUN?

48:10.421 --> 48:14.059
Liz: DON'T YOU WANT ME
TO BETTER MYSELF?

48:14.059 --> 48:16.227
YEAH,
BUT WHAT ABOUT ME?

48:16.227 --> 48:18.329
I NEVER GET
WHAT I WANT.

48:21.099 --> 48:22.333
WELL, WHO KNOWS?

48:22.333 --> 48:24.102
MAYBE MR. BIDERMAN
WILL GIVE ME A RAISE

48:24.102 --> 48:27.338
AFTER THIS AND WHO KNOWS
WHAT I CAN AFFORD THEN?

48:30.208 --> 48:33.111
I GUESS.
IF IT'S ONLY A WEEKEND.

48:35.380 --> 48:37.382
[SIGHS]

48:38.583 --> 48:41.386
THANK YOU.
GOOD.

48:44.055 --> 48:45.556
* WHAT A WORLD *

48:45.556 --> 48:49.294
* WHAT A LIFE
I'M LIVING FOR *

48:49.294 --> 48:51.896
* I'VE GOT
A NEW SONG I SING *

48:51.896 --> 48:54.465
* I CAN MAKE
THE RAIN GO *

48:54.465 --> 48:57.802
* ANY TIME I MOVE
MY FINGER *

48:57.802 --> 48:59.904
* LUCKY ME *

48:59.904 --> 49:03.041
* CAN'T YOU SEE
I'M IN LOVE? *

49:03.041 --> 49:04.809
* LIFE'S
A WONDERFUL THING *

49:04.809 --> 49:06.144
[DOOR CLOSES]

49:06.144 --> 49:09.380
* LONG AS I HOLD
THAT STRING *

49:09.380 --> 49:13.151
* I'D BE
A SILLY SO-AND-SO *

49:13.151 --> 49:17.255
* IF I SHOULD EVER
LET YOU GO *

49:17.255 --> 49:19.490
* I'VE GOT THE WORLD
ON A STRING *

49:19.490 --> 49:20.891
* SITTING
ON A RAINBOW *

49:20.891 --> 49:22.460
AAH! OH! HAVE
YOU EVER HEARD

49:22.460 --> 49:23.661
OF SUCH A THING
AS PRIVACY?

49:23.661 --> 49:25.330
SORRY.
WAIT!

49:25.330 --> 49:27.965
WAIT, YOU CAN'T
JUST LEAVE.

49:27.965 --> 49:29.634
WHAT DO I DO, THEN?

49:29.634 --> 49:32.203
TELL ME,
HOW DO I LOOK?

49:34.672 --> 49:35.973
YOU LOOK LIKE MY MOM.

49:35.973 --> 49:39.810
THE DRESS, THE DRESS!

49:39.810 --> 49:42.447
WOW.

49:43.581 --> 49:45.183
BE AN ANGEL.

49:47.985 --> 49:50.155
GUESS IT MUST'VE
COST A TON.

49:50.155 --> 49:52.657
DON'T YOU START
ON THAT, MISTER.

49:52.657 --> 49:56.161
* GOT THAT STRING
AROUND MY FINGER *

49:56.161 --> 49:58.963
* WHAT A WORLD *

49:58.963 --> 50:02.367
* YES, THIS IS
THE LIFE *

50:02.367 --> 50:06.771
* HEY, NOW, I'M IN LOVE *

50:06.771 --> 50:08.473
[BOTTLES CLINKING]

50:30.161 --> 50:31.496
Bobby:
"AND IN THE OPINION

50:31.496 --> 50:34.365
OF THIS REPORTER,
THE HAYWOOD-ALBINI FIGHT

50:34.365 --> 50:37.502
COULD TARNISH
A STERLING RECORD."

50:40.105 --> 50:43.141
I'D BACK HOLLYWOOD
HAYWOOD ANY DAY.

50:43.141 --> 50:45.943
TED? ARE YOU LISTENING?

50:45.943 --> 50:48.779
THEIR SENSES GROW KEENER.

50:48.779 --> 50:49.780
HMM?

50:52.317 --> 50:58.089
HEY, KIDDO,
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG TO SMOKE.

50:58.089 --> 51:00.125
SO, HOW LONG THIS TIME?

51:00.125 --> 51:03.228
BREAKING RECORDS
LEFT AND RIGHT.

51:03.228 --> 51:08.399
MM-HMM. WELL,
THEY'RE COMING CLOSER.

51:08.399 --> 51:11.102
WELL, THEY'RE DOING
A PRETTY GOOD JOB

51:11.102 --> 51:12.537
OF HIDING FROM ME.

51:12.537 --> 51:15.072
HAVEN'T SEEN
A SINGLE THING YET.

51:15.072 --> 51:19.177
GOOD. I'VE BEEN
WRONG BEFORE.

51:19.177 --> 51:21.379
[SIGHS]

51:21.379 --> 51:23.080
SO, GO ON
ABOUT THE FIGHT.

51:23.080 --> 51:26.617
OK. SO, THIS
OLD GUY, ALBINI,

51:26.617 --> 51:29.019
HE'S GONNA TAKE ON
HOLLYWOOD HAYWOOD

51:29.019 --> 51:30.755
TOMORROW NIGHT
IN NEW YORK.

51:30.755 --> 51:34.192
SOUNDS LIKE ALBINI'S
GONNA GET CREAMED.

51:34.192 --> 51:37.228
IT SURE DOES.

51:37.228 --> 51:39.096
WELL, I MIGHT
PLACE A BET.

51:39.096 --> 51:40.998
WE MAY TAKE A CAB
INTO BRIDGEPORT

51:40.998 --> 51:42.367
AFTER YOUR MOTHER'S
DEPARTURE.

51:42.367 --> 51:45.136
GET A BITE TO EAT.

51:45.136 --> 51:46.437
SEE A MOVIE.

51:46.437 --> 51:48.839
EVER HEAR OF
VILLAGE OF THE DAMNED?

51:48.839 --> 51:50.775
MM-MMM.

51:50.775 --> 51:55.713
IT'S ABOUT EVIL LITTLE KIDS
TAKEN OVER BY ALIEN FORCES.

51:56.781 --> 51:57.882
[BLOWS]

52:00.618 --> 52:01.619
THERE YOU GO.

52:03.254 --> 52:04.822
* HEY NONNY DING DONG *

52:04.822 --> 52:06.757
* ALANG ALANG ALANG *

52:06.757 --> 52:08.393
* BOOM BA-DOH *

52:08.393 --> 52:09.727
* BA-DOO BA-DOODLE-AY *

52:09.727 --> 52:11.696
* OH, LIFE COULD BE
A DREAM *

52:11.696 --> 52:12.930
* SH-BOOM *

52:12.930 --> 52:15.132
* IF I COULD TAKE YOU UP
IN PARADISE UP ABOVE *

52:15.132 --> 52:16.401
Carol: WHAT'S UP?

52:16.401 --> 52:18.002
* IF YOU WOULD TELL ME... *

52:18.002 --> 52:20.605
Carol: OH, NO, YOUR BIKE.

52:20.605 --> 52:22.106
* LIFE COULD BE A DREAM,
SWEETHEART *

52:22.106 --> 52:23.408
* HELLO, HELLO AGAIN *

52:23.408 --> 52:25.042
* SH-BOOM AND HOPIN'
WE'LL MEET AGAIN *

52:25.042 --> 52:26.644
Carol: STAY
RIGHT THERE, BOBBY.

52:26.644 --> 52:27.878
* SH-BOOM *

52:27.878 --> 52:30.381
* IF ONLY ALL MY PRECIOUS
PLANS WOULD COME TRUE *

52:30.381 --> 52:31.516
* SH-BOOM *

52:31.516 --> 52:32.617
* IF YOU WOULD
LET ME SPEND *

52:32.617 --> 52:34.485
* MY WHOLE LIFE
LOVIN' YOU *

52:34.485 --> 52:38.589
* LIFE COULD BE A DREAM,
SWEETHEART *

52:39.757 --> 52:41.992
* NOW EVERY TIME *

52:41.992 --> 52:43.661
* I LOOK AT YOU *

52:43.661 --> 52:46.130
* SOMETHING
IS ON MY MIND *

52:46.130 --> 52:47.498
* DAT-DAT-DAT
DAT-DAT-DUH *

52:47.498 --> 52:51.035
* IF YOU DO
WHAT I WANT YOU TO *

52:51.035 --> 52:53.070
* BABY, WE'D BE SO FINE *

52:53.070 --> 52:54.171
[LAUGHING]

52:54.171 --> 52:55.840
* OH, LIFE COULD BE
A DREAM *

52:55.840 --> 52:57.074
* SH-BOOM *

52:57.074 --> 52:59.744
* IF I COULD TAKE YOU UP
IN PARADISE UP ABOVE *

52:59.744 --> 53:00.745
* SH-BOOM *

53:00.745 --> 53:02.580
[BICYCLE BELL DINGING]

53:02.580 --> 53:05.750
Harry: OH!
[WOLF-WHISTLES]

53:05.750 --> 53:07.818
HEY, GERBER BABY!

53:10.688 --> 53:12.690
STILL WITH YOUR
LITTLE FAIRY?

53:12.690 --> 53:13.524
Willie:
YEAH!

53:13.524 --> 53:14.592
COME ON, CAROL.
LET'S GO HOME.

53:14.592 --> 53:16.794
WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

53:16.794 --> 53:17.695
THIS ISN'T FUNNY!

53:17.695 --> 53:20.465
WE THINK IT'S A RIOT,
GERBER BABY.

53:20.465 --> 53:21.266
UHH!

53:21.266 --> 53:22.467
HEY, LAY OFF HER!

53:22.467 --> 53:24.569
HEY, THE LITTLE
GUY'S A HERO.

53:24.569 --> 53:28.038
STOP ME, FAIRY.
BE A MAN.

53:28.038 --> 53:29.073
UHH!

53:29.073 --> 53:30.275
Harry:
I ASKED BEFORE

53:30.275 --> 53:31.276
HOW YOUR TITS
WERE COMING.

53:31.276 --> 53:33.344
NOW I WANNA FEEL
FOR MYSELF.

53:33.344 --> 53:34.912
Carol:
GET AWAY FROM ME!

53:34.912 --> 53:37.047
Bobby:
LEAVE HER ALONE!

53:37.047 --> 53:39.350
NAH. STILL JUST
A GERBER BABY.

53:39.350 --> 53:40.685
HA!
BASTARD.

53:40.685 --> 53:43.220
HEY, GUYS. LET'S
BEAT THIS QUEER UP.

53:43.220 --> 53:44.622
Richie: YEAH!

53:54.965 --> 53:56.434
Bobby: TED, GO HOME.

53:56.434 --> 53:59.770
WE'RE ALL GOING
HOME, BOBBY.

53:59.770 --> 54:03.541
WHO'S THAT,
YOUR FAIRY GODFATHER?

54:04.375 --> 54:06.243
Ted: RICHIE O'ROURKE,
WILLIE SHEARMAN,

54:06.243 --> 54:08.045
AND HARRY DOOLIN,

54:08.045 --> 54:10.781
THE UNHOLY TRIO
OF ST. GABE'S.

54:11.949 --> 54:13.384
HOW DO YOU KNOW
OUR NAMES?

54:13.384 --> 54:14.785
IF I WERE YOU, SON,
I'D COME HERE

54:14.785 --> 54:16.454
AND FIND OUT JUST
WHAT I DO KNOW.

54:28.132 --> 54:29.367
YOU'RE GOING
TO APOLOGIZE

54:29.367 --> 54:31.168
TO CAROL AND BOBBY.

54:31.168 --> 54:32.337
I DON'T THINK SO.

54:32.337 --> 54:33.404
SHALL I TELL YOU WHY

54:33.404 --> 54:35.406
YOU'RE GOING
TO APOLOGIZE?

54:35.406 --> 54:38.075
BECAUSE I KNOW
YOUR DARK SECRET.

54:38.075 --> 54:40.144
I WILL TELL
THE WORLD.

54:40.144 --> 54:42.547
I GOT NO SECRET.

54:42.547 --> 54:46.451
YOU LIKE CALLING
PEOPLE QUEER AND...

54:46.451 --> 54:49.554
FAIRY AND SUCH WORDS?

54:49.554 --> 54:51.889
LOOK IN MY EYES,
HARRY DOOLIN.

54:51.889 --> 54:54.759
TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE.

54:56.160 --> 54:57.428
TELL ME IF YOU
SEE SOMEONE

54:57.428 --> 54:59.430
ALL DRESSED UP IN
YOUR MOTHER'S CLOTHES,

54:59.430 --> 55:02.533
WHEN HE THINKS
NO ONE IS LOOKING.

55:02.533 --> 55:07.204
TELL THE WHOLE WIDE WORLD.

55:07.204 --> 55:09.907
NOW SAY,
"I'M SORRY, CAROL."

55:14.278 --> 55:15.713
I'M REAL SORRY, CAROL.

55:25.690 --> 55:26.691
Willie: WHAT'D
THE OLD GUY SAY?

55:26.691 --> 55:27.892
Richie: YEAH,
WHAT'D HE SAY?

55:27.892 --> 55:29.527
Harry: NOTHIN'.

55:33.063 --> 55:34.599
Carol:
THANK YOU, KIND SIR.

55:34.599 --> 55:36.467
Bobby: WHAT'D
YOU SAY TO HIM?

55:36.467 --> 55:38.469
Ted: OH, JUST
INTELLECTUAL CHIT-CHAT

55:38.469 --> 55:41.338
AMONG MEN OF GOOD WILL.

55:41.338 --> 55:43.007
Carol: TED?

55:43.007 --> 55:44.875
YES, SWEET CAROL?

55:44.875 --> 55:47.277
YOU'RE A VERY
STRANGE PERSON.

55:47.277 --> 55:49.380
SHH. TELL NO ONE.

55:49.380 --> 55:51.716
[CAROL LAUGHS]

55:51.716 --> 55:53.384
ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.
COME ON.

55:53.384 --> 55:55.486
OK. COME ON, NOW,
SETTLE DOWN.

55:55.486 --> 55:57.321
AND SULLY'S GOT THE BALL.

55:57.321 --> 55:58.322
OH, NO.

55:58.322 --> 55:59.657
OH, TOUCHDOWN.

55:59.657 --> 56:01.358
GET IN THE CAR.
ALL RIGHT.

56:01.358 --> 56:03.093
GET THE DOG.
[WHISTLES]

56:03.093 --> 56:04.128
[ARF]

56:04.128 --> 56:05.896
[ENGINE STARTS]

56:07.398 --> 56:09.366
Dad: AND AWAY WE GO.
BYE.

56:09.366 --> 56:10.868
BYE.

56:10.868 --> 56:12.703
HAVE A GOOD TRIP.

56:12.703 --> 56:14.104
SEE YA.

56:38.228 --> 56:40.498
OH, MY GOSH.
THE LOW MEN.

56:46.103 --> 56:47.638
[MEN LAUGH]

56:47.638 --> 56:49.173
HEY, SPORT.
WHERE'S THE LITTLE LADY?

56:49.173 --> 56:51.175
THERE HE IS,
RIGHT ON TIME.

56:51.175 --> 56:52.643
GIVE ME
A LITTLE SMOOCH.

56:52.643 --> 56:55.546
GET THE BAGS, DEAR.

56:55.546 --> 56:57.848
GOOD AFTERNOON.

56:57.848 --> 57:00.785
WELL, YOU LOOK GREAT.
HOW ARE YOU?

57:00.785 --> 57:01.586
FINE. OOH.

57:01.586 --> 57:02.453
HERE, I'LL TAKE THAT.

57:02.453 --> 57:03.854
OH, THANK YOU.

57:03.854 --> 57:05.389
CAN I GIVE YOU A HAND
WITH THOSE, SPORT?

57:05.389 --> 57:07.725
NO.

57:07.725 --> 57:10.728
GOT A REAL HELPFUL KID THERE.

57:10.728 --> 57:13.097
YES, HE'S A GOOD BOY.

57:13.097 --> 57:14.164
I'M SURE HE IS.

57:14.164 --> 57:16.433
WHAT A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

57:22.206 --> 57:24.208
MR. CUSHMAN, MR. DEAN.

57:24.208 --> 57:25.543
HEY, LIZ, GOOD DAY
FOR A DRIVE.

57:25.543 --> 57:28.012
YES, ISN'T IT?

57:28.012 --> 57:30.347
WOMEN.

57:30.347 --> 57:31.549
OH.

57:32.783 --> 57:35.285
THEY ALWAYS HAVE TO BRING
THE FARM, DON'T THEY?

57:35.285 --> 57:38.723
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY--

57:38.723 --> 57:41.358
CAN'T LIVE WITH 'EM...
CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT 'EM.

57:41.358 --> 57:43.427
CAN'T SHOOT 'EM.

57:43.427 --> 57:46.163
OUTSIDE MONTANA.

57:57.241 --> 57:59.610
[STARTS ENGINE]

57:59.610 --> 58:01.712
DON'T DO ANYTHING
I WOULDN'T DO, SPORT.

58:01.712 --> 58:04.615
BUT IF YOU DO,
NAME IT AFTER ME.

58:04.615 --> 58:07.184
[LAUGHTER]

58:07.184 --> 58:10.054
[THEME FROM A SUMMER PLACE
PLAYS ON RADIO]

58:14.424 --> 58:16.126
[LAUGHTER]

58:18.095 --> 58:22.132
Bobby:I TRUST HIM ABOUT AS FAR
AS I CAN SLING A PIANO.

58:22.132 --> 58:25.502
I'M WORRIED FOR MY MOM.

58:28.873 --> 58:31.075
I'M WORRIED FOR US ALL.

58:33.578 --> 58:36.280
Woman: DID YOU
SEE THOSE EYES?

58:36.280 --> 58:38.515
THEY'RE SO SCARY.
OH, I KNOW.

58:38.515 --> 58:39.750
Bobby:
WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

58:39.750 --> 58:41.018
Ted: HAD ENOUGH TO EAT?

58:41.018 --> 58:43.487
ARE YOU KIDDING,
AFTER THOSE HOT DOGS?

58:43.487 --> 58:47.091
WHAT DO THEY CALL
THIS PART OF TOWN?

58:47.091 --> 58:50.327
I'VE HEARD IT REFERRED
TO AS "DOWN THERE."

58:51.128 --> 58:54.765
YOU SEE, EVERY CITY
HAS A PLACE WHERE...

58:54.765 --> 58:57.668
YOUR LAST NAME
DOESN'T MATTER

58:57.668 --> 59:01.806
AND WINE COMES IN
A PAPER SACK, AND, UH...

59:01.806 --> 59:04.141
YOU CAN BUY ALMOST
ANYTHING YOU WANT

59:04.141 --> 59:07.745
IF YOU'VE GOT CASH
IN YOUR POCKET, THAT IS.

59:07.745 --> 59:09.546
HEY, COME ON.

59:10.648 --> 59:12.549
STAY CLOSE NOW.

59:12.549 --> 59:14.118
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THAT.

59:14.118 --> 59:16.587
I SHOULDN'T BRING YOU
INTO A PLACE LIKE THIS,

59:16.587 --> 59:19.890
BUT, UH, I CAN'T LEAVE YOU
OUT HERE, SO...

59:22.526 --> 59:24.729
HOLLYWOOD HAYWOOD
VERSUS EDDIE ALBINI

59:24.729 --> 59:26.631
TOMORROW NIGHT,
NEW YORK CITY.

59:26.631 --> 59:30.167
I'VE GOT MONEY TO BURN.
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

59:33.170 --> 59:34.639
NOT ONE STEP.

59:40.678 --> 59:42.913
KING ME. HA HA HA!

59:44.982 --> 59:48.653
TV: MAKING GOOD ON THE PROMISE.
HE PILES INTO BREON.

59:48.653 --> 59:50.087
HOW ABOUT YOU, BUDDY?
READY FOR ANOTHER?

59:50.087 --> 59:51.355
TV:
...HARDLY RECOGNIZE HIM

59:51.355 --> 59:54.992
AS THE ALMOST TIMID MAN
WHO LOST HIS TITLE.

59:54.992 --> 59:57.327
[MEN LAUGH,
POOL BALLS CLACK]

59:59.429 --> 01:00:03.567
HEY, KID,
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

01:00:03.567 --> 01:00:06.737
BOBBY. BOBBY GARFIELD.

01:00:06.737 --> 01:00:08.338
BEEN IN BEFORE?

01:00:08.338 --> 01:00:09.907
NO, MA'AM.

01:00:10.708 --> 01:00:12.643
YOU LOOK
KIND OF FAMILIAR.

01:00:14.879 --> 01:00:17.682
DID I KNOW YOUR FATHER,
MAYBE?

01:00:17.682 --> 01:00:21.852
MY FATHER'S DEAD.
HE DIED YEARS AGO.

01:00:21.852 --> 01:00:23.954
WAS HE BOBBY, TOO?

01:00:23.954 --> 01:00:26.657
BOBBY GARFIELD.
YES, MA'AM.

01:00:26.657 --> 01:00:29.026
HE'S JUST LIKE ME.

01:00:29.026 --> 01:00:31.628
YEAH. YEAH, HE WAS
A GOOD CUSTOMER.

01:00:31.628 --> 01:00:34.064
I LIKED HIM.

01:00:34.064 --> 01:00:39.069
HE USED TO STOP IN FOR A BEER
NOW AND THEN AND, UH...

01:00:40.104 --> 01:00:43.307
YOU KNOW--IT'S LIKE ON MONDAYS,
IT WAS JUST DEAD IN HERE,

01:00:43.307 --> 01:00:47.712
AND IN NO TIME FLAT,
WE WERE ALL LAUGHING.

01:00:48.512 --> 01:00:51.816
NOT A MEAN BONE IN HIS BODY.

01:00:52.616 --> 01:00:54.151
HE WAS GENEROUS, TOO.

01:00:54.151 --> 01:00:58.689
NOT TOO MANY LIKE THAT IN HERE.

01:00:58.689 --> 01:01:00.691
HE'D NEVER BUY A DRUNK A DRINK.

01:01:00.691 --> 01:01:01.992
YOU KNOW, I ADMIRED THAT.

01:01:01.992 --> 01:01:04.628
YEAH, AND HE ALSO NEVER MET
AN INSIDE STRAIGHT

01:01:04.628 --> 01:01:06.396
THAT HE DIDN'T LIKE.

01:01:06.396 --> 01:01:07.965
WHO TOLD YOU THAT?

01:01:07.965 --> 01:01:11.135
NOW, I REMEMBER
THE BIG LOSERS.

01:01:11.135 --> 01:01:13.904
AND MOST NIGHTS,
HE WALKED OUT OF HERE

01:01:13.904 --> 01:01:16.373
WITH A LITTLE BIT MORE
THAN HE CAME IN WITH.

01:01:18.308 --> 01:01:21.879
HE WAS A HELL OF
A CARD PLAYER, BOBBY WAS.

01:01:28.452 --> 01:01:30.254
KEEP THAT IF YOU WANT.

01:01:32.456 --> 01:01:34.258
HE'S HANDSOME,
DON'T YOU THINK?

01:01:35.059 --> 01:01:38.028
YOU GOT THAT
TO LOOK FORWARD TO.

01:01:40.965 --> 01:01:43.267
YOU GOT A GIRLFRIEND?

01:01:43.267 --> 01:01:45.235
YES, MA'AM.

01:01:45.235 --> 01:01:47.037
PRETTY?

01:01:47.037 --> 01:01:49.606
YES, MA'AM.
HER NAME'S CAROL.

01:01:49.606 --> 01:01:51.909
SHE'S A REAL HOTSY-TOTSY.

01:01:51.909 --> 01:01:56.947
HA HA HA!
A WHAT?

01:01:56.947 --> 01:01:59.083
LET'S GO, PARTNER.
TAXI'S WAITING.

01:01:59.083 --> 01:02:00.785
TED, LISTEN,
MY DAD CAME HERE.

01:02:00.785 --> 01:02:01.852
YEAH?

01:02:01.852 --> 01:02:03.120
AND HE DIDN'T LOSE
ALL OUR MONEY

01:02:03.120 --> 01:02:04.688
AND HE WAS GENEROUS
AND HE WAS FUNNY

01:02:04.688 --> 01:02:05.689
AND PEOPLE LIKED HIM.

01:02:05.689 --> 01:02:06.690
GOOD.

01:02:06.690 --> 01:02:08.058
ISN'T THAT A THING?

01:02:08.058 --> 01:02:10.961
YEAH. LUCKY FOR US
WE CAME IN HERE, I'D SAY.

01:02:10.961 --> 01:02:13.030
YES, IT IS
A WONDERFUL THING.

01:02:14.398 --> 01:02:16.033
SO HOW MUCH DID YOU BET?

01:02:16.033 --> 01:02:18.836
ALL I'VE GOT--$200 ON ALBINI.

01:02:18.836 --> 01:02:21.305
YOU THINK ALBINI CAN BEAT
HOLLYWOOD HAYWARD?

01:02:21.305 --> 01:02:23.841
YEAH, I THINK HE CAN
KNOCK HIM OUT.

01:02:23.841 --> 01:02:25.675
I BET ON HIM. 10-1 ODDS.

01:02:25.675 --> 01:02:27.878
DO YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT BOXING?

01:02:27.878 --> 01:02:30.948
NAH, NOTHING.
149 BROAD STREET. THANKS.

01:02:30.948 --> 01:02:32.482
I GUESS IT'LL BE
ON THE RADIO.

01:02:32.482 --> 01:02:35.352
WE'LL LISTEN TOMORROW NIGHT,
AND THEN WE'LL SEE.

01:02:35.352 --> 01:02:36.787
I HOPE YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING, TED.

01:02:36.787 --> 01:02:37.855
OH, NO, BOBBY,
HERE THEY COME.

01:02:37.855 --> 01:02:38.856
GET DOWN. QUICKLY,
OUT OF SIGHT.

01:02:38.856 --> 01:02:40.290
WHAT IS IT?

01:02:40.290 --> 01:02:42.226
JUST TAKE YOUR MIND AWAY.
DON'T BE FRIGHTENED, BOBBY.

01:02:42.226 --> 01:02:44.561
THINK OF SOMETHING ELSE.
JUST TAKE YOUR MIND AWAY.

01:02:44.561 --> 01:02:45.729
HOW? WHAT DO I DO?

01:02:45.729 --> 01:02:46.763
JUST THINK OF CAROL.
JUST THINK OF HER.

01:02:46.763 --> 01:02:48.098
DON'T EVER LET HER GO.

01:02:48.098 --> 01:02:51.568
THINK OF A HAPPY MEMORY.
THINK OF CAROL. [ECHOES]

01:02:51.568 --> 01:02:53.971
THINK OF A HAPPY MEMORY.
DON'T EVER LET HER GO.

01:02:53.971 --> 01:02:55.505
* FOR SHE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW *

01:02:55.505 --> 01:02:59.176
* FOR SHE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW *

01:02:59.977 --> 01:03:04.614
* THAT NOBODY CAN DENY *

01:03:04.614 --> 01:03:07.117
* THAT NOBODY CAN DENY *

01:03:07.117 --> 01:03:09.453
* FOR SHE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW *

01:03:09.453 --> 01:03:11.055
* FOR SHE'S
A JOLLY GOOD-- *

01:03:15.592 --> 01:03:19.563
* THAT NOBODY CAN DENY *

01:03:19.563 --> 01:03:22.032
[CHEERING]

01:03:34.244 --> 01:03:35.812
[CLICK]

01:03:39.183 --> 01:03:42.419
GOOD NIGHT, KIDDO.
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

01:03:42.419 --> 01:03:45.890
I'M SORRY I DIDN'T BELIEVE YOU
ABOUT THE LOW MEN.

01:03:45.890 --> 01:03:47.591
I KNOW.

01:03:49.293 --> 01:03:54.064
TED...MY FATHER NEVER
BOUGHT A DRUNK A DRINK.

01:03:54.865 --> 01:03:57.367
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN EXACTLY?

01:03:59.169 --> 01:04:03.207
IT MEANS HE WAS A GOOD MAN,
HE WAS HONEST,

01:04:03.207 --> 01:04:08.245
AND HE NEVER ADDED TO THE
TROUBLES OF THE WORLD, OK?

01:04:09.513 --> 01:04:11.315
GOOD NIGHT.

01:04:11.315 --> 01:04:12.917
GOOD NIGHT.

01:04:12.917 --> 01:04:15.185
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:04:22.927 --> 01:04:24.228
Announcer:
AND THERE'S THE BELL.

01:04:24.228 --> 01:04:26.463
HOLLYWOOD HAYWARD COMING OUT
THROWING PUNCHES,

01:04:26.463 --> 01:04:30.434
LITERALLY RUNNING IN. HE'S NOW
ATTACKING ALBINI AT WILL.

01:04:30.434 --> 01:04:33.070
ALBINI, ARMS HANGING
TO HIS BODY LIKE WEIGHTS,

01:04:33.070 --> 01:04:35.772
OCCASIONALLY THROWING
A WEAK PUNCH.

01:04:35.772 --> 01:04:37.241
THE PUNCHES ARE FLYING.
IT'S A FLURRY.

01:04:37.241 --> 01:04:39.809
OH, HOLLYWOOD IS JUST--
OH, MY GOODNESS!

01:04:39.809 --> 01:04:42.312
OUT OF NOWHERE,
A RIGHT PUNCH BY ALBINI

01:04:42.312 --> 01:04:46.216
HAS TAKEN HOLLYWOOD HAYWARD
TO THE HEAD AND TO THE MAT!

01:04:46.216 --> 01:04:49.353
THEY'RE COUNTING HIM OUT...
8, 9, 10. [BELL DINGS]

01:04:49.353 --> 01:04:51.788
OH, MY GOODNESS.
ONE OF THE MOST IMPROBABLE

01:04:51.788 --> 01:04:54.358
FINISHES TO A FIGHT
I HAVE EVER SEEN!

01:04:54.358 --> 01:04:56.526
ALBINI HAS BEATEN
HOLLYWOOD HAYWARD!

01:04:56.526 --> 01:05:00.164
THIS ONE HAS GOT TO BE
REVIEWED. ALBINI--

01:05:00.164 --> 01:05:01.198
[SHUTS OFF RADIO]

01:05:01.198 --> 01:05:07.972
WOW. YOU JUST WON
2,000 BUCKS.

01:05:07.972 --> 01:05:10.374
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

01:05:10.374 --> 01:05:14.711
HELLO? MRS. GARFIELD.
YES, FINE.

01:05:14.711 --> 01:05:16.981
I'LL GET HIM. BOBBY.
HMM?

01:05:16.981 --> 01:05:19.149
IT'S YOUR MOTHER.
OK.

01:05:21.851 --> 01:05:23.287
HI, MOM.

01:05:23.287 --> 01:05:24.088
HI, HONEY.

01:05:24.088 --> 01:05:25.755
HAVE YOU MISSED ME?

01:05:25.755 --> 01:05:27.224
OF COURSE I'VE MISSED YOU.

01:05:27.224 --> 01:05:30.294
BUT I'M TRYING NOT TO BE
TOO SAD ABOUT IT.

01:05:30.294 --> 01:05:34.531
OH, GOOD. NOW DON'T FORGET
TO BRUSH YOUR TEETH.

01:05:34.531 --> 01:05:35.632
I DID IT ALREADY.

01:05:35.632 --> 01:05:38.468
GOOD BOY. WELL, I CAN'T
BE CHATTING ALL NIGHT.

01:05:38.468 --> 01:05:40.670
THERE'S A COCKTAIL PARTY
FOR ALL OF US DELEGATES

01:05:40.670 --> 01:05:43.007
DOWNSTAIRS IN THE BALLROOM,
AND I DON'T...

01:05:43.007 --> 01:05:44.241
LET ME SEE
WHAT I CAN DO--

01:05:44.241 --> 01:05:46.410
ARE YOU STILL THERE?

01:05:46.410 --> 01:05:49.746
I DROPPED THE SILLY PHONE.
I LOVE YOU, BOBBY.

01:05:49.746 --> 01:05:51.781
DON--

01:05:51.781 --> 01:05:54.051
DO YOU REALIZE
I'D BE GIVING UP

01:05:54.051 --> 01:05:56.420
EVERYTHING I EVER
WORKED FOR?

01:05:56.420 --> 01:05:58.122
[LIZ STRUGGLING]

01:05:58.122 --> 01:05:59.956
THAT'S FUNNY.

01:06:02.559 --> 01:06:05.229
GOT CUT OFF.

01:06:15.172 --> 01:06:18.808
THAT 2,000...

01:06:18.808 --> 01:06:20.810
IT'S TRAVELING MONEY,
ISN'T IT?

01:06:20.810 --> 01:06:22.612
YEAH, IT IS.

01:06:27.517 --> 01:06:28.852
I LIED TO YOU, TED.

01:06:28.852 --> 01:06:31.988
I DIDN'T TELL YOU ABOUT
THE "LOST PET" SIGN I SAW.

01:06:31.988 --> 01:06:33.257
I KNOW.

01:06:34.058 --> 01:06:37.061
WHEN WILL YOU LEAVE?

01:06:37.061 --> 01:06:38.962
TOMORROW NIGHT,
WHEN YOUR MOTHER GETS BACK.

01:06:38.962 --> 01:06:42.032
COLLECT MY WINNINGS
FROM LEN FILES

01:06:42.032 --> 01:06:45.535
AT THE CORNER POCKET
AND GO.

01:06:47.871 --> 01:06:50.140
WILL I EVER SEE YOU AGAIN?

01:06:50.774 --> 01:06:52.276
NO.

01:06:53.077 --> 01:06:55.779
AND WISHING CAN'T MAKE IT SO.

01:07:04.321 --> 01:07:07.557
I DON'T WANT YOU TO GO.

01:07:11.928 --> 01:07:14.064
IT'S ALL FOR THE BEST, KIDDO.

01:07:14.864 --> 01:07:16.600
IT'S ALL FOR THE BEST.

01:07:29.679 --> 01:07:31.381
[CRICKETS CHIRP]

01:07:36.120 --> 01:07:37.821
[DOG BARKS]

01:07:41.991 --> 01:07:45.061
"IN YET ANOTHER
STARTLING DEVELOPMENT

01:07:45.061 --> 01:07:46.696
"IN WASHINGTON,

01:07:46.696 --> 01:07:47.897
"J. EDGAR HOOVER,

01:07:47.897 --> 01:07:51.635
"THE DIRECTOR OF THE FEDERAL
BUREAU OF INVESTIGATION,

01:07:51.635 --> 01:07:54.671
"TODAY ISSUED A STATEMENT
DENYING THAT BUREAU

01:07:54.671 --> 01:07:57.441
"WAS INVOLVED IN
RECRUITING PSYCHICS

01:07:57.441 --> 01:08:00.544
IN THE BATTLE
AGAINST COMMUNISM."

01:08:07.584 --> 01:08:11.821
THAT'S REALLY WHAT ALL THIS
IS ABOUT, ISN'T IT, TED?

01:08:18.295 --> 01:08:20.163
WANT A ROOT BEER?

01:08:20.163 --> 01:08:23.800
THAT'S THE ONLY GOOD THING
ABOUT YOU GOING--

01:08:23.800 --> 01:08:25.868
I CAN'T STAND THAT STUFF.

01:08:25.868 --> 01:08:28.572
HEH. YEAH, I KNOW.

01:08:29.372 --> 01:08:31.608
DO YOU KNOW EVERYTHING?

01:08:31.608 --> 01:08:32.841
NOPE.

01:08:33.676 --> 01:08:36.979
SO WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN YOU TOUCH PEOPLE?

01:08:36.979 --> 01:08:38.215
[OPENS REFRIGERATOR]

01:08:38.215 --> 01:08:40.417
OH, I PASS ON
A KIND OF WINDOW

01:08:40.417 --> 01:08:42.386
INTO OTHER PEOPLE'S MINDS.

01:08:43.220 --> 01:08:47.357
IS THAT WHY THEY WANT YOU,
THIS WINDOW?

01:08:47.357 --> 01:08:51.661
YEAH. I KNOW CERTAIN THINGS,
SEE CERTAIN THINGS.

01:08:51.661 --> 01:08:54.029
SOME THINK OF IT
AS A GIFT, BUT TO ME,

01:08:54.029 --> 01:08:55.432
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN A BURDEN.

01:08:55.432 --> 01:08:59.169
WHAT I SEE
HAS A VALUE FOR SOME.

01:08:59.169 --> 01:09:02.738
MAYBE I ESCAPED THEM
THIS TIME. THANKS.

01:09:03.740 --> 01:09:05.140
CHEERS.

01:09:05.140 --> 01:09:06.142
[BOTTLES CLINK]

01:09:06.142 --> 01:09:08.812
YOUR GOOD HEALTH.

01:09:08.812 --> 01:09:11.180
AH! AH, WELL.

01:09:11.180 --> 01:09:14.718
WE'RE ALL JUST
PASSING THROUGH, KIDDO.

01:09:15.551 --> 01:09:18.388
JUST PASSING THROUGH,
THAT'S ALL.

01:09:20.790 --> 01:09:24.194
TELL CAROL I'D LIKE TO SAY
GOOD-BYE TO HER, TOO.

01:09:24.194 --> 01:09:25.629
SURE.

01:09:29.999 --> 01:09:31.067
[DOOR OPENS]

01:09:31.067 --> 01:09:33.036
HEY, BOBBY!
YEAH?

01:09:33.937 --> 01:09:37.274
I THINK YOU SHOULD GO
AND FIND HER NOW.

01:09:39.175 --> 01:09:40.344
OK.

01:09:40.344 --> 01:09:42.479
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:09:59.963 --> 01:10:01.798
[RUMBLING]

01:10:12.942 --> 01:10:14.378
[RUMBLING]

01:10:14.378 --> 01:10:16.212
HEY, BOBBY.

01:10:16.212 --> 01:10:17.514
UM, IS CAROL HOME?

01:10:17.514 --> 01:10:19.283
NO, SHE WENT DOWN
TO THE RAVINE

01:10:19.283 --> 01:10:21.351
TO READ HER BOOK
BY THAT TREE.

01:10:23.353 --> 01:10:25.555
[WATER TRICKLING]

01:10:36.266 --> 01:10:38.468
[TRAIN RUMBLING]

01:10:48.712 --> 01:10:51.180
YOU DON'T SCARE ME,
BOBBY GARFIELD.

01:10:51.180 --> 01:10:52.181
WELL...

01:10:52.181 --> 01:10:54.751
IF IT ISN'T
THE GERBER BABY.

01:10:54.751 --> 01:10:56.720
[BANGING]

01:10:58.288 --> 01:11:01.024
AAH! NO! PLEASE! AAH!

01:11:02.592 --> 01:11:04.294
HARRY?

01:11:04.294 --> 01:11:05.762
UNHH!

01:11:06.896 --> 01:11:08.465
SHH.
NO!

01:11:10.033 --> 01:11:11.401
[PANTS AND GRUNTS]

01:11:11.401 --> 01:11:13.303
[LIZ SCREAMS]

01:11:13.303 --> 01:11:14.904
OHH!

01:11:14.904 --> 01:11:16.039
[GRUNTS]

01:11:17.040 --> 01:11:18.308
Carol: AAH! DON'T!

01:11:20.910 --> 01:11:22.512
Bobby: CAROL. CAROL!

01:11:23.313 --> 01:11:24.914
[RIPPING]

01:11:26.049 --> 01:11:27.317
[GRUNTS]

01:11:28.918 --> 01:11:30.654
[FLAPPING]

01:11:36.192 --> 01:11:37.527
Bobby: CAROL!

01:11:39.195 --> 01:11:41.130
CAROL!

01:11:41.130 --> 01:11:43.400
IS EVERYTHING OK?

01:11:44.568 --> 01:11:46.235
[CRYING]
HE HIT ME, BOBBY!

01:11:46.235 --> 01:11:47.737
HE HIT ME HARD.

01:11:47.737 --> 01:11:50.974
IT'S OK.
I'LL GO GET HELP, OK?

01:11:50.974 --> 01:11:51.975
NO, PLEASE!

01:11:51.975 --> 01:11:53.377
DON'T LEAVE ME
ALONE.

01:11:53.377 --> 01:11:55.111
HE MIGHT COME BACK.

01:11:55.111 --> 01:11:57.313
IT'LL BE OK.
CAN YOU WALK?

01:11:57.313 --> 01:11:59.248
[GASPS]
I DON'T KNOW.

01:11:59.248 --> 01:12:01.217
JUST TRY, OK?
MAYBE.

01:12:01.217 --> 01:12:02.386
WE'LL TRY.

01:12:02.386 --> 01:12:03.853
[CRYING] OHHH!

01:12:05.355 --> 01:12:06.890
[CRYING]
IT'LL BE OK.

01:12:06.890 --> 01:12:08.057
IT'S OK.

01:12:08.057 --> 01:12:10.093
HERE, TRY
AND STAND UP, OK?

01:12:10.093 --> 01:12:12.095
[CRYING]

01:12:13.129 --> 01:12:14.864
HERE, CAN YOU STAND UP?

01:12:20.604 --> 01:12:22.539
OK, CAROL, HERE'S
WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO.

01:12:22.539 --> 01:12:24.273
YOU HAVE TO GET
ON MY BACK, OK?

01:12:24.273 --> 01:12:25.442
BOBBY, I CAN'T!

01:12:25.442 --> 01:12:28.244
YES, YOU CAN.
YES, YOU CAN.

01:12:28.244 --> 01:12:29.713
[CRYING]

01:12:29.713 --> 01:12:30.847
YOU CAN.

01:12:30.847 --> 01:12:33.917
YOU--YOU HAVE TO THINK
ABOUT SOMETHING ELSE, OK?

01:12:36.085 --> 01:12:38.187
HERE, GET ON MY BACK.

01:12:38.187 --> 01:12:39.456
REMEMBER AT SCHOOL

01:12:39.456 --> 01:12:41.958
WHEN WE WERE PLAYING
PIGGYBACK DURING RECESS?

01:12:41.958 --> 01:12:42.759
YES.

01:12:42.759 --> 01:12:44.694
THIS IS JUST
LIKE THAT, OK?

01:12:47.196 --> 01:12:48.632
[GRUNTS]

01:12:51.334 --> 01:12:53.537
[BOBBY GRUNTING]

01:12:57.841 --> 01:12:58.842
UNHH.

01:13:01.044 --> 01:13:02.412
COME ON.

01:13:06.149 --> 01:13:08.452
[CROWD CHANTING]

01:13:08.452 --> 01:13:10.454
Ted: BRONKO NAGURSKI.

01:13:10.454 --> 01:13:11.755
NAGURSKI.

01:13:15.324 --> 01:13:17.527
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:13:19.228 --> 01:13:21.197
Bobby: 10 YARDS...

01:13:21.197 --> 01:13:22.432
7 YARDS...

01:13:22.432 --> 01:13:24.668
[BOBBY GRUNTS, CROWD CHEERS]

01:13:28.472 --> 01:13:30.674
Bobby:
NOTHING COULD STOP HIM.

01:13:31.875 --> 01:13:33.443
[PANTING]

01:13:48.191 --> 01:13:49.659
[HORN HONKS]

01:13:50.460 --> 01:13:52.662
[TRAIN RUMBLES]

01:14:02.305 --> 01:14:03.773
TED!

01:14:03.773 --> 01:14:05.308
TED!

01:14:05.308 --> 01:14:07.243
TED, HELP.

01:14:07.243 --> 01:14:08.444
[CRYING]

01:14:08.444 --> 01:14:10.179
I THINK HER RIGHT ARM
IS BROKEN.

01:14:10.179 --> 01:14:11.247
COME ON, CAROL.
[YELLS]

01:14:11.247 --> 01:14:12.582
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

01:14:13.382 --> 01:14:15.018
OPEN THE DOOR.

01:14:15.018 --> 01:14:16.285
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

01:14:16.285 --> 01:14:18.488
[CRYING]

01:14:25.461 --> 01:14:26.563
[GASPS]

01:14:26.563 --> 01:14:27.931
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

01:14:29.198 --> 01:14:30.266
[CRYING] OW, MY ARM!

01:14:30.266 --> 01:14:31.400
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

01:14:31.400 --> 01:14:33.603
BOBBY, YOU TAKE HER HAND,
ALL RIGHT?

01:14:34.838 --> 01:14:35.839
[WHIMPERS]

01:14:35.839 --> 01:14:36.940
OH, YEAH.

01:14:38.074 --> 01:14:40.644
ONE GREAT BIG BOY
AGAINST ONE LITTLE GIRL.

01:14:41.645 --> 01:14:44.080
HE WAS PROBABLY
SO AFRAID OF YOU.

01:14:44.080 --> 01:14:46.449
PROBABLY THOUGHT YOU HAD
THE HEART OF A LION.

01:14:46.449 --> 01:14:49.385
[CRYING]
HE HURT ME, TED.

01:14:49.385 --> 01:14:51.655
I KNOW.
BELIEVE ME, I KNOW.

01:14:51.655 --> 01:14:53.557
NOW LISTEN, CAROL.

01:14:53.557 --> 01:14:56.125
I'VE GOT TO LOOK AT
YOUR SHOULDER, UNDERSTAND?

01:14:56.125 --> 01:14:58.628
DON'T WANT TO HURT YOU.
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

01:14:59.428 --> 01:15:00.930
OH, MY.

01:15:00.930 --> 01:15:01.731
[CAROL GASPS]

01:15:01.731 --> 01:15:03.833
HE BROKE MY ARM.

01:15:03.833 --> 01:15:05.301
I DON'T THINK
IT'S BROKEN.

01:15:05.301 --> 01:15:06.603
I THINK IT'S
JUST DISLOCATED.

01:15:06.603 --> 01:15:09.138
AND I THINK
I CAN FIX IT.

01:15:10.306 --> 01:15:11.575
[WHIMPERS]

01:15:11.575 --> 01:15:14.611
ARE YOU A DOCTOR,
TED?

01:15:14.611 --> 01:15:16.379
NO, I'M NOT A DOCTOR.

01:15:16.379 --> 01:15:19.583
BUT AS YOU NOTED,
I'M VERY STRANGE.

01:15:19.583 --> 01:15:21.951
SO WHO KNOWS
WHAT I CAN DO.

01:15:21.951 --> 01:15:24.220
DO YOU HAVE
THE HEART OF A LION?

01:15:24.220 --> 01:15:26.322
[CRYING]

01:15:26.322 --> 01:15:27.957
ALL RIGHT.

01:15:27.957 --> 01:15:30.860
JUST CLOSE YOUR EYES
AND TRY TO RELAX.

01:15:30.860 --> 01:15:33.797
BOBBY, GIVE ME YOUR BELT.

01:15:35.031 --> 01:15:37.967
NOW, CAROL, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT PAIN DOES?

01:15:37.967 --> 01:15:38.868
Carol: HMM?

01:15:38.868 --> 01:15:41.204
IT RISES.
IT TRAVELS UP THE BODY.

01:15:41.204 --> 01:15:43.773
THAT'S IT. THANK YOU.

01:15:43.773 --> 01:15:45.809
NOW, LISTEN TO ME, CAROL.

01:15:45.809 --> 01:15:47.977
JUST LISTEN AND RELAX.

01:15:47.977 --> 01:15:50.146
I WANT YOU TO BITE DOWN
HARD ON BOBBY'S BELT.

01:15:50.146 --> 01:15:53.516
YOU'RE GOING TO BITE DOWN
ON BOBBY'S BELT

01:15:53.516 --> 01:15:55.785
AND CATCH THE PAIN.

01:15:56.586 --> 01:15:58.387
NOW, RELAX.

01:15:58.387 --> 01:16:00.389
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

01:16:00.389 --> 01:16:02.058
KEEP THEM CLOSED.

01:16:02.058 --> 01:16:05.294
YOU'RE SAFE.
JUST BREATHE IN.

01:16:05.294 --> 01:16:06.796
BREATHE OUT,
THAT'S IT.

01:16:06.796 --> 01:16:08.732
THERE'S NO PAIN.

01:16:08.732 --> 01:16:11.300
JUST LISTEN TO MY VOICE.

01:16:13.069 --> 01:16:16.305
I CAN SENSE THEM
CLOSING IN ON ME, BOBBY.

01:16:16.305 --> 01:16:17.841
I KNOW.

01:16:17.841 --> 01:16:20.276
THERE'S SIGNS
EVERYWHERE.

01:16:20.276 --> 01:16:21.110
HERE WE GO.

01:16:21.110 --> 01:16:23.479
BITE DOWN HARD
AND CATCH THE--

01:16:23.479 --> 01:16:25.048
HERE WE GO.

01:16:25.048 --> 01:16:26.315
[SCREAMS]

01:16:26.315 --> 01:16:28.417
SHH.

01:16:28.417 --> 01:16:29.619
ALL RIGHT.

01:16:30.419 --> 01:16:31.454
THERE.

01:16:31.454 --> 01:16:32.455
TED?

01:16:32.455 --> 01:16:33.623
YEAH?

01:16:33.623 --> 01:16:35.959
IT DOESN'T HURT ANYMORE.

01:16:35.959 --> 01:16:38.695
YOU DO HAVE
THE HEART OF A LION.

01:16:38.695 --> 01:16:39.696
THANK YOU.

01:16:39.696 --> 01:16:41.564
YOU DID WELL, KIDDO.

01:16:41.564 --> 01:16:44.100
Liz: WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON IN HERE?

01:16:44.100 --> 01:16:47.036
Bobby: OH, MOM, LOOK
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU.

01:16:47.036 --> 01:16:49.706
GOD! TAKE YOUR HANDS OFF
THAT LITTLE GIRL, YOU BASTARD!

01:16:49.706 --> 01:16:52.241
MOM! HE DIDN'T
DO ANYTHING BAD!

01:16:52.241 --> 01:16:53.576
HOW DARE
YOU TOUCH HER?

01:16:53.576 --> 01:16:54.844
YOU SON
OF A BITCH!

01:16:54.844 --> 01:16:56.145
MOM, NO!
HE DIDN'T HURT HER!

01:16:56.145 --> 01:16:58.114
I FOUND HER IN THE PARK,
AND I BROUGHT HER HERE

01:16:58.114 --> 01:16:59.582
SO THAT TED
COULD HELP HER!

01:16:59.582 --> 01:17:00.984
GO TO YOUR ROOM!
AND YOU!

01:17:00.984 --> 01:17:03.687
YOU FILTHY OLD MAN.
YOU ARE GOING TO JAIL!

01:17:03.687 --> 01:17:04.854
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU
WAS TERRIBLE.

01:17:04.854 --> 01:17:06.790
IT DIDN'T HAPPEN
TO HER, THOUGH.

01:17:07.791 --> 01:17:09.558
WHY IS HER BLOUSE
OPEN?

01:17:09.558 --> 01:17:10.593
SO HE COULD
FIX HER SHOULDER!

01:17:10.593 --> 01:17:11.895
I TOLD YOU TO GO
TO YOUR ROOM!

01:17:11.895 --> 01:17:14.063
Carol: WHAT BOBBY SAID
WAS TRUE!

01:17:16.966 --> 01:17:20.003
LET'S GO IN THE BATHROOM
AND GET YOU CLEANED UP.

01:17:20.003 --> 01:17:22.706
HE CARRIED ME
UP THE HILL.

01:17:22.706 --> 01:17:25.308
TED TOOK
MY PAIN AWAY.

01:17:25.308 --> 01:17:27.176
DON'T YOU TOUCH HER!

01:17:27.176 --> 01:17:28.277
[CAROL MOANS]

01:17:28.277 --> 01:17:29.846
GO IN THE BATHROOM.
I'LL BE THERE IN A SECOND.

01:17:29.846 --> 01:17:31.080
I'M CALLING THE POLICE,

01:17:31.080 --> 01:17:33.182
AND I'M TELLING THEM
EVERYTHING I JUST SAW.

01:17:33.182 --> 01:17:35.985
WHY DON'T YOU TELL THEM
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

01:17:37.120 --> 01:17:39.122
YOU WEREN'T THERE.
YOU COULDN'T KNOW.

01:17:40.123 --> 01:17:41.657
I--I KNOW.

01:17:41.657 --> 01:17:43.727
I KNOW YOU DIDN'T
REALIZE THE SEMINAR

01:17:43.727 --> 01:17:45.494
WAS GOING TO INVOLVE
LIQUOR AND SEX.

01:17:45.494 --> 01:17:47.196
AND I KNOW YOUR SON
IS GROWING UP

01:17:47.196 --> 01:17:49.866
WHILE YOUR MIND IS
ON OTHER THINGS.

01:17:53.770 --> 01:17:56.305
I'M GOING TO TAKE
THAT CHILD HOME,

01:17:56.305 --> 01:17:58.942
AND YOU BETTER NOT BE HERE
WHEN I GET BACK.

01:18:06.615 --> 01:18:07.751
BE CAREFUL, TED.

01:18:07.751 --> 01:18:09.585
I'LL BE FINE,
DON'T WORRY.

01:18:09.585 --> 01:18:11.755
WHERE WILL YOU GO
TILL IT'S DARK?

01:18:11.755 --> 01:18:12.889
AH, TO THE DINER

01:18:12.889 --> 01:18:15.491
NEAR THE CORNER POCKET,
I GUESS.

01:18:15.491 --> 01:18:16.960
PICK UP
MY WINNINGS LATER.

01:18:16.960 --> 01:18:19.228
I WANT TO GO
WITH YOU.

01:18:20.429 --> 01:18:22.565
BOBBY,
COME INSIDE, PLEASE.

01:18:22.565 --> 01:18:24.768
DO AS SHE SAYS,
KIDDO.

01:18:32.441 --> 01:18:34.377
[DOOR SHUTS]

01:18:34.377 --> 01:18:36.412
[FOOTSTEPS]

01:19:11.480 --> 01:19:16.552
Liz: AH, YES, IS THIS,
UH, HOUSITONIC 5-8-3-7?

01:19:17.553 --> 01:19:21.290
YES, WELL, I HAVE SOME
INFORMATION FOR YOU...

01:19:21.290 --> 01:19:23.392
ABOUT BRAUTIGAN.

01:19:23.392 --> 01:19:27.496
YOU CAN FIND HIM AT
THE CORNER POCKET TONIGHT

01:19:27.496 --> 01:19:29.332
IN BRIDGEPORT.

01:19:30.233 --> 01:19:33.402
YES. NOW,
THERE'S A REWARD--

01:19:33.402 --> 01:19:35.171
HELLO? HEL--

01:19:36.873 --> 01:19:38.174
[SIGHS]

01:19:38.975 --> 01:19:40.443
[HANGS UP PHONE]

01:19:40.443 --> 01:19:42.278
BASTARDS. [SIGHS]

01:19:51.120 --> 01:19:52.255
Man on TV:
THEN FIND THE SHERIFF

01:19:52.255 --> 01:19:53.722
AND TELL HIM
TO BE READY FOR TROUBLE.

01:19:53.722 --> 01:19:55.024
Second man on TV:
WHERE DO WE MEET YOU?

01:19:55.024 --> 01:19:56.860
NEAR THE CROSSROADS
ON THE OTHER SIDE OF TOWN.

01:19:56.860 --> 01:19:58.161
GOOD.

01:19:58.161 --> 01:19:59.328
Woman on TV:
ROY, STOP IT.

01:19:59.328 --> 01:20:00.729
WHAT'S IT GOING
TO BE, HONEY?

01:20:00.729 --> 01:20:02.265
YOU'LL FIND OUT
WHEN IT'S FINISHED.

01:20:02.265 --> 01:20:04.868
AS IF I DIDN'T KNOW.
MY FAVORITE DESSERT.

01:20:04.868 --> 01:20:06.870
WE HAVE TO CELEBRATE
TODAY SOMEHOW.

01:20:06.870 --> 01:20:08.071
DID YOU GET
THE MONEY ALL RIGHT?

01:20:08.071 --> 01:20:09.906
YOU BET.
I SOLD ALL TEN.

01:20:09.906 --> 01:20:12.475
THERE IS $1,000.

01:20:12.475 --> 01:20:13.542
GOLD!

01:20:15.411 --> 01:20:17.346
Ted: WHEN YOUR MOTHER
WRITES "BAD"

01:20:17.346 --> 01:20:20.016
UNDER A MENTAL PICTURE
OF SOMEONE,

01:20:20.016 --> 01:20:21.484
SHE WRITES IT IN INK.

01:20:22.485 --> 01:20:24.020
[CASH REGISTER RINGS]

01:20:24.020 --> 01:20:25.188
I MEAN, I KNEW THAT,

01:20:25.188 --> 01:20:27.857
BUT I DIDN'T THINK
SHE'D BETRAY ME.

01:20:32.996 --> 01:20:34.898
SEE, I NEED
THE MONEY TO SURVIVE,

01:20:34.898 --> 01:20:39.202
AND I...CAN'T GO BACK
TO THE CORNER POCKET.

01:20:40.736 --> 01:20:44.573
AND I NEED TIME
TO THINK, AND, UH...

01:20:44.573 --> 01:20:45.975
THERE ISN'T ANY.

01:20:50.914 --> 01:20:52.315
[COUGHS]

01:20:54.117 --> 01:20:55.885
HERE'S WHAT YOU DO.

01:20:57.053 --> 01:20:58.421
WRITE A NOTE FOR ME.

01:20:58.421 --> 01:20:59.989
A NOTE?

01:21:00.890 --> 01:21:03.159
YEAH.
TO THE CORNER POCKET.

01:21:03.159 --> 01:21:05.394
I'LL GET YOU
YOUR MONEY.

01:21:07.330 --> 01:21:11.034
I'M NOT SURE THIS
IS A GOOD IDEA, BOBBY.

01:21:11.034 --> 01:21:12.835
TED, TAKE MY HANDS.

01:21:12.835 --> 01:21:14.537
HUH?

01:21:14.537 --> 01:21:15.804
DON'T WORRY.

01:21:15.804 --> 01:21:19.108
I WON'T LET
THE BOGEYMEN GET YOU.

01:21:21.510 --> 01:21:22.511
[CHUCKLES]

01:21:35.724 --> 01:21:36.892
[DIAL TONE]

01:21:36.892 --> 01:21:38.527
[DIALS]

01:21:47.070 --> 01:21:49.272
[LINE RINGING]

01:21:53.542 --> 01:21:54.910
Man on phone: HELLO?

01:21:58.081 --> 01:22:00.283
MAY I HELP YOU?

01:22:00.283 --> 01:22:02.018
LISTEN,
THIS IS ABOUT BRAUTIGAN.

01:22:02.018 --> 01:22:03.486
HE'S GONE.
HE TOOK THE TRAIN.

01:22:03.486 --> 01:22:04.720
I SAW HIM GO.

01:22:04.720 --> 01:22:07.190
STAY OUT
OF THIS, KID.

01:22:07.190 --> 01:22:09.392
BRAUTIGAN'S
OUR BUSINESS.

01:22:12.661 --> 01:22:14.297
DON'T HURT HIM.

01:22:16.599 --> 01:22:19.835
PLEASE, DON'T HURT HIM.

01:22:19.835 --> 01:22:22.005
GO HOME, BOBBY.

01:22:22.005 --> 01:22:24.207
[LINE DISCONNECTS,
DIAL TONE]

01:22:29.578 --> 01:22:31.147
Woman: HEY!

01:22:32.048 --> 01:22:33.882
HEY, HONEY.

01:22:33.882 --> 01:22:36.085
[PEOPLE TALKING
INDISTINCTLY]

01:22:38.021 --> 01:22:40.689
Woman: YEAH, COME ON
OVER HERE, BABY.

01:22:46.795 --> 01:22:48.231
[GLASS SHATTERS]

01:22:56.339 --> 01:22:57.606
[PANTS]

01:23:12.521 --> 01:23:13.522
[GASPS]

01:23:19.195 --> 01:23:21.397
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

01:23:21.397 --> 01:23:23.132
[BANGING]

01:23:41.417 --> 01:23:42.418
[GASPS]

01:23:43.852 --> 01:23:45.554
[CREAK]

01:24:03.939 --> 01:24:06.375
[SIGHS]

01:24:11.247 --> 01:24:13.449
[PATRONS CHATTERING]

01:24:15.118 --> 01:24:15.951
[DOOR OPENS]

01:24:15.951 --> 01:24:17.286
TED, I GOT THE MONEY.

01:24:18.087 --> 01:24:19.088
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

01:24:19.088 --> 01:24:21.290
[CAR DRIVES AWAY]

01:24:24.827 --> 01:24:26.295
[MUMBLES]
[WHINES]

01:24:29.832 --> 01:24:31.334
TED!

01:24:31.334 --> 01:24:32.601
TED!

01:24:38.040 --> 01:24:39.642
[GASPS]

01:24:43.346 --> 01:24:44.480
TED!

01:24:46.081 --> 01:24:48.083
TED.

01:24:48.083 --> 01:24:50.052
TED!

01:24:50.052 --> 01:24:51.320
TED!

01:24:51.320 --> 01:24:53.922
I WOULDN'T HAVE MISSED
A MINUTE OF IT, BOBBY!

01:24:53.922 --> 01:24:55.124
NOT A SINGLE MINUTE!

01:24:56.992 --> 01:24:58.794
NOT FOR
THE WHOLE WORLD, BOBBY!

01:24:58.794 --> 01:25:00.696
TED!

01:25:00.696 --> 01:25:02.231
TED!

01:25:06.702 --> 01:25:07.870
TED.

01:25:26.088 --> 01:25:27.456
WHERE ON EARTH
HAVE YOU BEEN?

01:25:27.456 --> 01:25:29.192
I'VE BEEN WORRIED SICK
ABOUT YOU!

01:25:29.192 --> 01:25:31.827
I'M ALL SAFE
AND SOUND.

01:25:31.827 --> 01:25:32.895
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA

01:25:32.895 --> 01:25:33.996
WHAT YOU JUST
PUT ME THROUGH?

01:25:33.996 --> 01:25:35.898
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE YOU WERE.

01:25:35.898 --> 01:25:39.635
YOU ONLY THINK
ABOUT YOURSELF!

01:25:39.635 --> 01:25:40.436
[SIGHS]

01:25:40.436 --> 01:25:42.205
BOBBY.
TED'S GONE.

01:25:42.205 --> 01:25:44.407
I'LL NEVER
SEE HIM AGAIN.

01:25:45.274 --> 01:25:47.843
SO YOU GOT EVERYTHING
YOU WANTED. HAPPY NOW?

01:25:47.843 --> 01:25:51.214
BOBBY, THERE'S NO MONEY.
I DON'T HAVE A JOB.

01:25:51.214 --> 01:25:52.915
THERE'S PLENTY
OF MONEY NOW!

01:25:54.650 --> 01:25:56.919
SEE HOW GREAT
IT WORKED OUT,

01:25:56.919 --> 01:25:58.287
TURNING HIM IN?

01:25:58.287 --> 01:26:00.956
I DID--I DID IT FOR YOU.
IT WAS FOR YOUR OWN GOOD.

01:26:00.956 --> 01:26:04.660
YOU LIE!
YOU ALWAYS LIE.

01:26:06.061 --> 01:26:08.431
[CRYING] MY FATHER
WAS A GOOD MAN,

01:26:08.431 --> 01:26:11.033
AND PEOPLE
LIKED HIM.

01:26:11.033 --> 01:26:12.067
[SIGHS]

01:26:12.067 --> 01:26:14.303
EVERYONE LIKED HIM
EXCEPT YOU.

01:26:14.303 --> 01:26:17.306
YOU NEVER LIKED ME,
EITHER.

01:26:17.306 --> 01:26:19.041
AND THEN
I FIND A FRIEND,

01:26:19.041 --> 01:26:20.409
A GROWN-UP FRIEND
OF MY OWN,

01:26:20.409 --> 01:26:24.547
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
I LOVED HIM.

01:26:25.948 --> 01:26:27.583
YOU DIDN'T
JUST BETRAY HIM.

01:26:27.583 --> 01:26:29.485
YOU BETRAYED
BOTH OF US.

01:26:38.527 --> 01:26:39.762
[GASPS]

01:26:40.963 --> 01:26:42.331
BOBBY...

01:26:48.837 --> 01:26:50.839
[WATER TRICKLING]

01:26:53.075 --> 01:26:55.177
Bobby: TED GOT IT RIGHT.

01:26:55.177 --> 01:26:57.546
IT ISN'T ALL ATLANTIS.

01:26:59.348 --> 01:27:03.352
MY MOTHER GOT A JOB
OUTSIDE OF BOSTON,

01:27:03.352 --> 01:27:04.887
AND I WAS UPSET,
OF COURSE.

01:27:04.887 --> 01:27:08.491
BUT ONE THING...
I WASN'T AFRAID.

01:27:08.491 --> 01:27:10.959
I HAD TED
TO THANK FOR THAT.

01:27:12.227 --> 01:27:15.664
HEY, GET OUT OF HERE.
THIS IS MY PLACE NOW.

01:27:15.664 --> 01:27:18.767
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.
THIS IS EVERYBODY'S PARK.

01:27:18.767 --> 01:27:20.002
YES, I CAN.

01:27:23.472 --> 01:27:25.374
LITTLE BOBBY GARFIELD.

01:27:25.374 --> 01:27:29.412
WHERE'S YOUR FAIRY GODFATHER
NOW WHEN YOU NEED HIM?

01:27:37.886 --> 01:27:39.488
[PANTS]
OHH!

01:27:43.025 --> 01:27:44.026
OHH!

01:27:45.260 --> 01:27:46.595
[GRUNTING]

01:27:46.595 --> 01:27:48.297
GET OFF!

01:27:48.297 --> 01:27:49.498
[HARRY CRYING]

01:27:50.433 --> 01:27:52.167
[CRYING AND GRUNTING]

01:27:52.167 --> 01:27:54.503
THAT WAS FOR
THE GERBER BABY!

01:27:57.172 --> 01:27:58.541
[GROANS]

01:28:06.882 --> 01:28:08.884
[JINGLING]

01:28:12.421 --> 01:28:15.023
* WHEN PURPLE-COLORED
CURTAINS *

01:28:15.023 --> 01:28:17.626
* MARK THE END OF DAY *

01:28:17.626 --> 01:28:20.062
* I'LL HEAR YOU, MY DEAR *

01:28:20.062 --> 01:28:22.798
* AT TWILIGHT TIME *

01:28:23.866 --> 01:28:27.370
* DEEPENING SHADOWS
GATHER SPLENDOR *

01:28:27.370 --> 01:28:29.938
* AS DAY IS DONE *

01:28:29.938 --> 01:28:33.376
* FINGERS OF NIGHT
WILL SOON SURRENDER *

01:28:33.376 --> 01:28:36.278
* THE SETTING SUN *

01:28:36.278 --> 01:28:38.814
* I COUNT THE MOMENTS,
DARLING *

01:28:38.814 --> 01:28:41.484
* TILL YOU'RE
HERE WITH ME *

01:28:41.484 --> 01:28:44.019
* TOGETHER AT LAST *

01:28:44.019 --> 01:28:46.655
* AT TWILIGHT TIME *

01:28:48.223 --> 01:28:50.459
HEY, DO YOU NEED
ANY HELP?

01:28:50.459 --> 01:28:52.461
I'M FINE.

01:28:52.461 --> 01:28:54.463
[JINGLING COINS]

01:28:54.463 --> 01:28:56.865
[TWILIGHT TIME
PLAYS QUIETLY]

01:29:12.781 --> 01:29:14.950
SO, DO YOU THINK YOU
COULD EVER SEE YOUR WAY

01:29:14.950 --> 01:29:16.419
TO FORGIVING ME?

01:29:21.424 --> 01:29:23.692
I'M WORKING ON IT, MOM.

01:29:26.762 --> 01:29:27.896
[SIGHS]

01:29:53.789 --> 01:29:57.426
CAROL,
WE'RE LEAVING NOW.

01:29:57.426 --> 01:29:58.827
OH, NO.

01:30:00.463 --> 01:30:03.432
HERE. IT'S WHERE I'LL BE
IN MASSACHUSETTS.

01:30:03.432 --> 01:30:05.167
WILL YOU WRITE TO ME?

01:30:05.167 --> 01:30:06.935
OF COURSE.

01:30:06.935 --> 01:30:08.504
I'LL WRITE TO YOU.

01:30:09.572 --> 01:30:11.840
I'LL PROBABLY
BE HOMESICK.

01:30:12.808 --> 01:30:15.010
I'LL NEVER
FORGET YOU.

01:30:21.316 --> 01:30:24.753
WAS IT YOU WHO BEAT UP
HARRY DOOLIN?

01:30:24.753 --> 01:30:26.221
MM-HMM.

01:30:26.221 --> 01:30:28.390
GOOD.

01:30:28.390 --> 01:30:29.792
GOOD.

01:30:40.402 --> 01:30:41.604
CAROL, WAIT.

01:30:41.604 --> 01:30:43.038
I CAN'T. NOT NOW.

01:30:45.073 --> 01:30:46.008
BUT I--

01:30:46.008 --> 01:30:48.176
I LOVE YOU, TOO,
BOBBY GARFIELD.

01:30:49.812 --> 01:30:51.680
BUT I HAVE TO GO
MAKE THE SALAD.

01:30:55.050 --> 01:30:56.184
[DOOR SLAMS]

01:30:58.587 --> 01:31:00.088
[HORN HONKS]

01:31:02.491 --> 01:31:05.494
Radio: 9:35, 25 MINUTES
BEFORE 10:00 ON WKMD.

01:31:05.494 --> 01:31:08.531
SERVING UP THE BIGGEST HITS
WITH THE PLATTERS.

01:31:08.531 --> 01:31:12.535
* ONLY YOU *

01:31:12.535 --> 01:31:13.869
[DOOR OPENS]

01:31:13.869 --> 01:31:17.439
* CAN MAKE THIS WORLD
SEEM RIGHT *

01:31:17.439 --> 01:31:19.074
SO, WHAT ARE WE
GONNA DO, BOBBY-O?

01:31:19.074 --> 01:31:22.845
THE BEST WE CAN, MOM.
THE BEST WE CAN.

01:31:25.413 --> 01:31:28.717
WELL, TIME AND TIDE
WAIT FOR NO MAN.

01:31:28.717 --> 01:31:30.519
YOU KNOW, BEN JONSON
CALLED TIME

01:31:30.519 --> 01:31:32.087
"THE OLD
BALD CHEATER."

01:31:32.087 --> 01:31:33.522
WHO'S BEN JONSON?

01:31:33.522 --> 01:31:34.923
AN ENGLISH WRITER.

01:31:34.923 --> 01:31:38.627
FOOLISH ABOUT MONEY...
AND GIVEN TO FLATULENCE.

01:31:38.627 --> 01:31:40.462
FLATULENCE?

01:31:40.462 --> 01:31:41.930
[FARTING NOISE]

01:31:41.930 --> 01:31:44.800
BOBBY GARFIELD!
[LAUGHS]

01:31:44.800 --> 01:31:49.271
* AND FILL MY HEART
WITH LOVE *

01:31:49.271 --> 01:31:53.742
* FOR ONLY YOU *

01:31:55.310 --> 01:31:57.412
[TRAIN WHISTLES AND RUMBLES]

01:31:57.412 --> 01:31:59.615
[JINGLING]

01:32:14.763 --> 01:32:17.566
Girl: HEY! I DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD BE IN THERE.

01:32:18.601 --> 01:32:20.035
IT'S NOT SAFE.

01:32:20.035 --> 01:32:22.971
OH, I USED TO LIVE HERE
WHEN I WAS A KID.

01:32:28.076 --> 01:32:29.444
YOU LIVED HERE LONG?

01:32:29.444 --> 01:32:31.647
[CHUCKLES]
ONLY MY WHOLE LIFE.

01:32:32.781 --> 01:32:35.117
OH, WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

01:32:40.055 --> 01:32:42.124
WAS YOUR MOTHER...

01:32:43.291 --> 01:32:44.827
WAS SHE...

01:32:46.061 --> 01:32:49.064
WAS SHE CAROL?
CAROL GERBER?

01:32:50.432 --> 01:32:53.501
MY MOM'S DEAD.
SHE DIED YEARS AGO.

01:32:53.501 --> 01:32:55.237
I WAS SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

01:32:57.906 --> 01:33:00.743
WE NEVER KEPT IN TOUCH
LIKE WE SAID WE WOULD.

01:33:05.280 --> 01:33:08.016
[CHUCKLES] MY GOD!

01:33:08.016 --> 01:33:10.753
YOU'RE THE BOY
ON THE FERRIS WHEEL?

01:33:12.220 --> 01:33:13.656
MOM TOLD ME ABOUT THAT.

01:33:13.656 --> 01:33:16.659
AND SHE PROMISED
SHE'D NEVER TELL ANYONE.

01:33:18.994 --> 01:33:21.596
SHE SAID...
YOU WERE BEAUTIFUL.

01:33:21.596 --> 01:33:25.200
OH, WELL.

01:33:25.200 --> 01:33:26.935
ONE OF US WAS.

01:33:57.399 --> 01:33:58.667
[SIGHS]

01:33:58.667 --> 01:34:00.268
[SOFTLY MOANS]

01:34:02.070 --> 01:34:04.372
YOU CAN KEEP THAT
IF YOU WANT.

01:34:08.510 --> 01:34:10.378
I'M BOBBY.

01:34:11.714 --> 01:34:13.315
MOLLY.

01:34:13.315 --> 01:34:14.917
MOLLY.

01:34:19.988 --> 01:34:22.991
SHE HAD THE HEART
OF A LION.

01:35:05.067 --> 01:35:07.736
Bobby: I NEVER HEARD
FROM TED BRAUTIGAN AGAIN.

01:35:08.837 --> 01:35:11.406
NOT THAT
I DIDN'T THINK OF HIM.

01:35:11.406 --> 01:35:13.575
I ALWAYS HAVE...

